e and deliver a great speech. In addition, international experts and coaches in communication like Jeremey Donovan, Sebastian Lora and Jean-Roch Michel will jump in on various occasions to share their research, illustrate techniques and ensure you get a well-rounded view of the success factors in public speaking.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course is taught in English, but there will be subtitles to help our MOOCers. The total workload will be about 2h/week, dedicated to watching video lectures, taking quizzes and completing recommended exercises.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course enables participants to learn tricks and tips to enhance their presentations and therefore feel comfortable while presenting. In addition to taking the course and exchanging with peers, we expect participants to develop an understanding of different communication styles which they can subsequently apply to their daily conversations.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo prior knowledge is necessary to take this course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1 - Discover your communicative style[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 1 - My experience  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2 - What makes a good presentation?[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 3.1 - Communicative styles of your audience[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 3.2 - Personal communicative audit - exercise  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2 - Structure your presentation[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 1 - Meet your audience    [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2.1 - Preparation technique 1: 6 w's[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2.2 - Preparation technique 2: Visual mapping  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2.3 - Preparation technique 3: Communication circle[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 3 - Reason [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 argue or how to win your battles  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3 - Write and design your presentation**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 1 - Tell us a story  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2 - Be funny  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 3.1 - Write well[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 3.2 - Write well: rhetorical resources  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 4 - Be elegant or how to prepare your visuals  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBonus track: elevator pitch  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4 - Rehearse your presentation[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 1 - Practice makes excellence[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2.1 - Prepare f