mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I learn**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnParticipants will be able to understand and apply certain methods of idea generation on any self chosen topic. For example, they will understand and apply methods such as  Mindmapping [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Clustering, 6-3-5, World Cafe [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 DeBono Hats, Concept Mapping, Scenario Techniques ( e.g. STEEP), Roadmapping and many more - always in a structured process.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo prior knowledge needed, only being curious and interested in a topic which could be further developed.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Introduction: Get the picture out of your head!**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStrategic Innovation Management, Idea Generation Process, Innovation Process and fuzzy front end[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Design Factors**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhat's in your picture? [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31mDesign Aspects, Methods, Sources [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Defining your Search Space**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLandscape or portrait?[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m Context Definition, Agenda Setting, Problem Representation [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Scenario**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhat's my perspective? [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31mDefinition of Scenario Topic, STEEP / PESTEL Analysis, Influence Factors and Descriptors[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 5[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Future Assumptions: Using watercolour or oil?[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPresent Situation and Future Assumptions, Bundling Projection, Interpretation of Scenario, Wild Cards, SWOT, Proposals for Action[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 6[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Scenario based Roadmapping**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhat to draw when? [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31mDefinition of a Roadmapping Topic, Needs Analysis, Analysis of Potentials[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 7[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp; Establishing your roadmap**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSketching your picture![1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m Establishing a Roadmap, Consistency Analysis and Evaluation[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately 4 hours per week for watching lecture videos, taking quizzes and completing homework assignments. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-01-21T09:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-03-11T16:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/c7c54158-29ce-4599-aec1-250361a684ba/70144181274000.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:329,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mArchitecture 101 - Part I[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mFrom nothingness to place: To learn to stare, observe and see places like architects do. To transform a place into a state of mind. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Architecture 101:**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnArchitecture to convert a place into a state of mind.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApparently a simple task, actually a fairly tricky operation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo (try to) understand, we split our journey into three parts. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course is about part 1: from nothingness to place ([part 2][1] is from place to space, [part 3][2] is from space to architecture).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhat is a place?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhat is space?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHow do we make space? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHow do we prepare our mind to make space?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWithout a concept, we can[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt have a place.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWithout a place, we can[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt have space. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWithout a space, we can[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt have architecture...[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf we want to create space, in the first instance, it has to happen in our mind. When a conceptual vision takes form in our minds, a place (with its own spatial features) is born.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnArchitecture 101 is an introduction to space and architecture through 101 exercises. A six-month journey divided into 3 courses [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31monline[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m on iversity (part 1, part 2 and part 3), one final exhibition / graduation party. If you are still alive after all of this daunting process, there will be a one-week workshop [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31moffline[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m, where we will go one step beyond.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**In short:**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPart 1: From Nothingness to Place (Jan 5 to Feb 28, we will work in 2d) [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPart 2: From Place to Space (Mar 2 to Apr 25, we will work in 3d)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPart 3: From Space to Architecture (Apr 27 to Jun 20, we will work in scale 1 to 1)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnExhibition / Graduation at Abadir, in Sicily (Jun 19 to Jun 21, we set up our fancy exhibition)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWorkshop: Architecture 101 Summer Camp at Abadir, in Sicily (Jun 22 to Jun 26, we build for real).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Architecture 101 (part 1: from nothingness to place)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo start our journey, we will deal with the absence of space and place. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSomething that could be defined as [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mnothingness[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAs Ang Lee or Paul Valery would respectively say : [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mThe source of all the material comes from nothingness.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mGod made everything out of nothing, but the nothingness shows through.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn a different way, Ludwig Wittgenstein taught us that when things have no name, they don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt exist. Hence in order to understand things, we have to start with worlds in which things have no name. Pieces of music without sound. Televisions without signal.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will go through the process of shaping meaning. Articulate and complex meanings, defining relationships between mind and bodies, bodies and places. Little by little, we will encounter places and see the world taking shape. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAll of this, using a [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mhands-on[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m system (you will by doing).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 1: taking pictures[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 2: learning to sketch[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 3: making collages[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 4: observing the weather[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 5: shaping diagrams[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 6: drawing maps[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 7: passing an exam[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 8: taking a break[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Learning Objectives**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo see places like architects do.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo understand the principles upon which we convert a place into a state of mind.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will explore nothingness, void and negative space.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will learn to name things, we will learn how to invent place (as we wrote before, when things have no name, they cannot exist).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will learn to stare, observe and see. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will learn a significative amount of extremely interesting (and totally useless) things.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAll of the above refers to the conceptual part of our course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, since we love having our students making practical things, you will also learn lots of technical things using a number of interesting applications.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**At the end, what do I make?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnA booklet (with a given proportion, size, appearance) where you will collect all of your visual experiments. Each booklet devoted to a specific [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mplace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m. If one thousand people finish this part 1, we will have a fabulous collection of 1000 booklets.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Prior Knowledge**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Important thing!**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn terms of prior knowledge, nothing in particular is required. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHowever, in terms of technical equipment, this course will be easier to follow for those with access to a smartphone or tablet. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe shaped this course for a very specific kind of student. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur imaginary student is a gent (or gentle lady) who accesses our content via his/her smartphone. Of course you can follow us via a desktop, make homework at home on your table. Yet, the way we intended the whole thing is for someone who takes the whole course (including doing homework) via a smartphone (or tablet).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBetween 3 and 7 hours a week. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFrom Monday to Friday, for a total of 6 weeks, you will receive an email with a 15 second-video to watch (to get you in the mood), and a pdf with some instructions for completing an assignment and a series of references (to go deeper in the subject at hand).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, you will get to work on your assignment. Once you complete your assignment, you will upload it to the iversity platform and share it on your preferred social media account(s). Ideally Instagram.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, during the weekend, we will give you some time to catch up.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAre you ready?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn:-)  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://iversity.org/de/courses/architecture-101-part-ii[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://iversity.org/de/courses/architecture-101-part-iii[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-01-05T11:23:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-02-28T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mactive[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/5508b94a-4b18-46b8-8f8f-d4a7ef4cfb51/70227001209820.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:84,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDisasters and Ecosystems: Resilience in a Changing Climate[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDisasters kill people, destroy infrastructure, damage ecosystems and undermine development. Climate change is expected to aggravate existing disaster risks. Ecosystem-based approaches for disaster risk reduction can be a strategy with multiple benefits.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis MOOC enhances knowledge and skills for tackling complex issues such as resilience and transformation, sustainable development, ecosystem management, disaster risk reduction, climate change adaptation and how they can be operationalized. It will benefit disaster managers and practitioners, climate change adaptation professionals, development planners, project implementers and policy makers. The course will be delivered through a series of lectures and case studies, quizzes, peer-reviewed exercises, along with additional study materials provided to the students. Lectures will be available through videos as well as online documents and will be geared for students who may not have access to high speed internet so they can follow the course. Students will be provided the opportunity to enhance their critical thinking through real life and fictitious problem solving exercises. Each week will feature an international expert who will be available to respond to questions and interact with students. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAfter completion of the course, the participant will be able to:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Define basic concepts of disasters, disaster risk reduction, climate change adaptation and[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnresilience.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Recognize key linkages between ecosystems, disaster risk reduction and climate change[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnadaptation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Recognize the linkages and overlaps between ecosystem based disaster risk reduction and[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnecosystem based adaptation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Identify various ecosystem based tools in reducing disaster risk and climate change adaptation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Identify key international agreements, organizations and initiatives related to disaster risk reduction, and climate change adaptation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Apply concepts and tools of ecosystem-based disaster risk reduction (Eco-DRR) and ecosystem based adaptation (EbA). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Evaluate costs and benefits of different type of measures for reducing disaster risks.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Design your own ecosystem-based project for increasing resilience and reducing climate risks.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThere are no prerequisites, just some willingness to learn about this innovative topic!  It is however true that it will help if you have heard about disasters and climate change before starting.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course is structured in two parts: [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe ***leadership track***, which is tailored for busy professionals or students curious about the topic. The leadership track will run three weeks. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe ***expert track*** is for professionals and students who seek more in-depth learning and skill development in applying ecosystem-based tools for disaster risk reduction and adaptation. The expert track will run 12 weeks with 3 weeks for the final assignment, peer review process and course wrap-up.  Each unit has several quizzes, a concise background document for further reading, a discussion forum, supplementary videos with interviews with international experts and short documentary videos from around the world.  In addition, world leaders were interviewed for our MOOC.  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Outline and Schedule**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1. Leadership track [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m introduction  (Week 1)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 1. Disasters and Ecosystems: Resilience in a Changing Climate - why take this course?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 2. Introduction to disasters, risk reduction and climate change[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2.  Leadership track [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m  linking disasters, climate change and ecosystems, Part 1 (Week 2)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 3. Links between disasters, disaster risk reduction, adaptation and key international actors[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 4. Principles and challenges of ecosystem-based disaster risk reduction (Eco-DRR) and adaptation (EbA)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3. Leadership track [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m disaster management, resilience and ecosystems (Week 3)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 5. Ecosystem management contributions pre- and post-disasters[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 6. Managing resilience and transformation[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4. Expert track [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m linking disasters, climate change and ecosystems, Part 2 (Weeks 4[1;35m\\[0m[31mu00265)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 7. Linking ecosystems and humans to disasters[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 8. Principles of systems thinking and using natural systems for disaster risk reduction[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 9. Putting Ecosystem-based disaster risk reduction (Eco-DRR) into practice [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 5.  Putting theory into practice (Weeks 5 [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 6)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 10. Linkages between Eco-DRR and EbA[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 11. Putting Ecosystem-based adaptation into practice [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 peer review assignment [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 6. Ecosystem-based tools for disaster risk reduction [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m introduction (Week 7)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 12. Incorporating ecosystems in risk assessments[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 13. Ecosystems and spatial tools for risk reduction[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 7. Most common Eco-DRR tools (Week 8)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 14. Principles of spatial planning and community-based tools for Eco-DRR[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 8. Most common Eco-DRR tools (Week 9)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 15. Sustainable land and water management tools for Eco-DRR [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 16. Ecological engineering for disaster risk reduction and climate change adaptation[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 9. Economics, valuation and policy issues (Week 10)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 17. Economic tools for Eco-DRR [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 18. Principles of mainstreaming ecosystem based disaster risk reduction into national policies, strategies, plans and projects[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 10.  Resilience and transformation [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 final assignment (Weeks 11 -13)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 19. Approaches for operationalizing resilience[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 20. Problem solving assignment [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m peer review of assignments [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 11.  Course wrap-up (Week 13)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUnit 21. Course wrap-up and forum discussions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Who is teaching this course?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnInstructors include international faculty members from Germany, Egypt, Austria and Switzerland, supported by a line-up of expert guest lecturers and exclusive interviews with world leaders in the field of climate change, disaster risk reduction and environment:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mtDr. Achim Steiner (Executive Director of UNEP)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mtMs. Margareta Wahlstr[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xB6[0m[31mm (Special Representative of the Secretary-General of the United Nations for Disaster Risk Reduction)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mtDr. Rajendra Pachauri  (Chancellor of TERI University)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mtMs. Julia Marton-Lef[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31mvre (Director General of the International Union for the Conservation of Nature 2007-2015[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Some FAQs**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**How much time do I need to put in taking the MOOC?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn total, we estimate that a total of 40-50 hours is needed to complete the MOOC (taking both the Leadership and Expert Tracks), which will also depend on your background and English fluency. The MOOC is roughly equivalent to a 1 [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31mweek in-class training course. This estimate is based on completing the video lectures, guest video lectures, reading materials and exercises.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDo I have to be online at specific times?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo. While new modules will be released sequentially on specific dates, you need not come online simultaneously. The lectures are not webcast real-time and you can choose the time you wish to watch them. However, there will be some deadlines for assignments and peer-to-peer reviews.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Will there be exams involved?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Leadership track has quizzes so you can self-check your knowledge level as you go. This is, however, not a precondition for progressing to the next module. And you may, however, choose to revisit a module if you feel you did do not perform satisfactorily in a module. The Expert track has two short peer-reviewed assignments and one final peer-reviewed exercise where you will be designing your own project! The peer reviewed exercises will provide an environment for interaction between course participants. You are welcome to use any other communication tool to facilitate group assignments. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What are the interactive features in this MOOC?** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIversity has a community discussion forum that will be followed by course instructors and a roster of international [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mExperts of the week[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m. The Iversity platform offers all participants the chance to give feedback on the MOOC itself but also to start discussions on any topic related to the MOOC. During the enrolment stage of the MOOC, you will be asked to fill out some basic information about yourself and be invited to actively participate in the community discussion forum. You can also post notices on the MOOC [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mmeeting point[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m or to join discussions that others have started. There will thus be ample opportunity to connect with other participants for information exchanges[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**MOOC by**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![enter image description here][1] ![enter image description here][2][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**In cooperation with**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![enter image description here][3] ![enter image description here][4][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Contributions by** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![enter image description here][5][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Supported by**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![enter image descriptio