[31m:221,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mSerious Game Design and Development [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDid you know that games can be serious? Serious Games take advantage of the engaging characteristics of games to develop the players' knowledge, personal and social skills. Join us and learn how to design and how to develop a serious game![1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course addresses the design and development of Serious Games. Serious Games are games that do not have entertainment as the main purpose but rather an educational, awareness raising, training, advertisement or other [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mserious[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m purpose that benefits from the engaging context that games provide to motivate the users. Serious Games have been typically used in education, training, health, defense and other sectors. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnMOOC students will go through all the steps of the development of a Serious Educational Game from selecting the idea and binding it with learning goals to the development and testing of the game prototype in an environment that does not require programming skills. The programme of study will allow students to understand the process of idealizing, designing, developing, testing and delivering a game. At the same time, students will benefit from a hands-on experience, working in intercultural and interdisciplinary teams, exploiting the expertise of an international team of participating teachers and industry experts.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course objective is to allow students understand the process of idealizing, designing, developing, testing and delivering a serious game.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn the end, students will be able to...[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Understand and comment the main concepts of game culture and digital game theory[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Analyze game taxonomies and identify the specific characteristics of each game type[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Carry out analyses and user tests to understand users[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31m demands and needs and convert them into serious game requisites (including learning objectives for game-based learning)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Understand and apply serious game methodologies[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Understand the concepts related to game play, game flow, interactive narratives, storytelling and apply them in practice to develop an addictive game [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - List the main tools (game editors) available to develop games and to identify the best one for a specific purpose[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Use a specific game editor to develop a serious game[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Idealize, design, develop, test and deliver a serious game[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBasic computer and internet skills[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately 5 hours per week for watching video lectures, taking quizzes and completing homework assignments.  [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-01-13T00:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-03-31T00:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/5e7a2fe3-97e5-451a-8031-cfeb2729acd1/70269605998120.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:209,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mBusiness Analysis 101[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mHave you ever been in a situation where you needed to demonstrate some sort of analytical thinking? Have you ever had to solve some complex problem? If so, you were a secret practitioner of Business Analysis activities and didn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt even realise.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOver the last 10 to 15 years, the inception of new products and services has steered corporations to manage this development in a much more efficient manner in order to meet customer demand.  This introspection within the business community was comprised of two elements:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn1.) Can one identify the deficiencies in previous workings in order to overcome the shortcomings?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn2.) What is the employee skillset required in order to ensure proper deployment of these new customer needs?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe inception of the Business Analysis profession was a result of this changed situation as well as an overall classification of those competencies that were already being practiced in the enterprise.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course takes a look at the competencies required of a Business Analysis. In addition, you will be exposed to the following elements tied to the subject matter:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The typical business analysis path, starting with a problem statement, the requirements tied to the need to be addressed and a definition of the most robust solution possible.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The tie between the enterprise strategy and business analysis activities.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The relationship between needs and current processes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Document analysis and the importance of historical data[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The means by which elicitation is performed[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Solutions, business cases and decisions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Business Analysis and quality[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - System thinking and estimations[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course is intended to give you a general overview of what this discipline entails and can act as a springboard into more detailed study at a future date.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAccording to the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, a 19% job growth rate for Business Analysts is expected till 2022, and the outlook for the rest of the world should be higher still.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What are the underlying competencies of a Business Analyst?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The importance of stakeholder management within the business analysis domain.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Where within the enterprise can a business analyst be found?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - In which sectors are business analyst competencies being practiced?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is the importance of processes within the business analysis domain?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Why business transformation starts with an understanding of the current processes deployed within an organization.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What are some of the tools and techniques used to create, evaluate, modify and analyze processes?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What are organizational process assets and enterprise environmental factors?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What tools and techniques are used to create and analyze enterprise artifacts?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is elicitation, and what techniques does a BA have at her disposal?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The importance of traceability within an organization.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is the relationship between solutions and risks?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What elements should one consider when evaluating numerous solution possibilities?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is the cost of quality?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Why is quality management important to a Business Analyst?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What quality management tools and techniques can a Business Analyst use?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is the Deming Cycle?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - How are the 7 Basic Quality Tools deployed?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What means of estimation does a BA have at her disposal?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Business Analysis, data and forecasting.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is the theory of constraints?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Game theory, crowdsourcing and the Business Analyst.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo prior knowledge is required.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe **first week**, we look at what makes a Business Analyst; what are the underlying competencies, how a BA fits in the organization, the concept of stakeholders and organizational readiness, and lastly in which sectors those BA competencies can be found.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn **week #2**, we look at process analysis; the importance of process documentation, the relationship between processes and business transformation, process diagramming and process modeling.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 3** takes us to document analysis. We look at Organizational Process Assets and Enterprise Environmental Factors, Impact Analysis, business rules, traceability and other elements that prepare you to move on in your BA path.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur **fourth week** takes us to the world of requirements gathering; what elicitation is, the different ways of performing the exercise and what steps need to be followed within requirements analysis. So that[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms week 4, requirements gathering.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week # 5** concerns all things tied to solutions; the relationship between a problem statement and a solution, the evaluation of multiple solutions, and how we pick the best one.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur **sixth week** views the subject of quality management. What cost does quality have? What are the seven basic quality tools and of course what this all has to do with Business Analysis?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur **last week** takes us into the realm of system thinking and estimation. How important is probability within our BA activities?  What is the theory of constraints? We will perform a walkthrough on subject such as crowdsourcing and game theory, and that pretty much covers our last week.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately 4 hours per week for watching lecture videos and completing quizzes and homework assignments. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-01-15T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-03-19T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/bb5b6199-4bdf-4f36-82ec-07c39e1a652b/69916976517020.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:154,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mStonehenge[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mThe most spectacular monument of the Neolithic is now a British icon and a World Heritage Site. Explore 5,000 years of Stonehenge and discover your own response to this enigmatic stone circle.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhen was Stonehenge built? Who built it? How was it built? Why was it built? Answers cannot be promised to all of these, but we can get better at asking the questions and work towards solutions. We can look at how people have responded to Stonehenge. Most of all we can begin to think about what Stonehenge means to us.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - To understand present archaeological thinking about Stonehenge.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - To evaluate responses to Stonehenge in art, literature, music, architecture and culture.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - To consider your own response to Stonehenge, expressed through two peer-evaluated mini-essays.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need too know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo entry requirements. This MOOC is open to all.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1: The Stonehenge Landscape**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStonehenge as a landscape of prehistoric sites. A historical context: the Mesolithic, the Neolithic and the building of the Stonehenge.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2: Who built Stonehenge?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTheories: when, by whom, how and why.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3: Stonehenge Problems**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnContext - the Stonehenge landscape: problems with transportation and erection. Part destruction - why and how?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4: Responses to Stonehenge** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAn array of responses: Geoffrey of Monmouth (1138); the antiquarian tradition, the temple and astronomic alignments traditions; various amateur theories; the archaeological traditions.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStonehenge, Woodhenge: monuments in a landscape[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 5: Cultural Contexts**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStonehenge in fiction, poetry, music, art and popular culture.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 6: Stonehenge Today**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStonehenge as a cultural icon, emblem of Britain, World Heritage site and sacred space.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBlick Mead as the cradle of Stonehenge.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 7: Reassessing Stonehenge** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWritten activity as an assessment[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 8: Responses to Stonehenge**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnExamination of students' responses through their essays. Integration of blog, Wiki, Twitter and eBook as a way of continuing the discussion after the course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately two hours per week for watching video lectures, completing quizzes and homework assignments. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-01-21T00:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-03-11T00:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/32d0550d-b69e-4e62-8943-69ea8fd1a038/70096858924300.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:233,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mHuman Rights: Global [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Local Protection[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mWhen and why have human rights become effectively central? The course will answer such questions, stressing the multi-level dimensions of the work for human rights.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHuman rights are a complex issue. Their protection and promotion involve a number of actors: from international organisations to local communities, from governments to civil society. Human rights affect all aspects of our life, as individuals (as women, men, children, refugees, workers[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA6[0m[31m) and as members of a community. This MOOC provides students with critical knowledge concerning the norms, institutions and procedures tasked to promote and protect human rights. Students will acquire the knowledge needed to actively join the global debate on fundamental rights and to avail themselves of the existing legal and institutional tools set up for their implementation. The MOOC introduces to the human rights legal framework in a multi-disciplinary and multi-level perspective, helping students to approach real-life scenarios with competence and cultural and ethical awareness.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents are expected to acquire a sound knowledge of the international system of human rights protection, and of the opportunities for human rights promotion and protection that are practically available at the national and local levels. The skills acquired can be preparatory for further specialisation on this subject. Finally, students will be able to apply the acquired knowledge and skills to real scenarios, including in relation to their everyday life.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe MOOC is mainly addressed to people from all over the world who have a background in political science, international relations and/or international law. The course, however, includes a general introductory chapter explaining the main issues, concepts and scenarios at stake. For this reason the MOOC is also open to people actively engaged on the ground that do not have a specific academic or educational background.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1 - The basics**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Chapter aims to introduce the course and starts addressing (and providing some preliminary answers) some basic questions: What are human rights? Who is involved in their protection? Why are human rights a global priority? How can effectively be protected?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2 - The UN and human rights**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe focus is on the evolution of the UN commitment in human rights protection based on three pillars: positivisation, monitoring and mainstreaming.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3 - The UN human rights machinery**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe analysis deals with the UN mechanisms for the protection of human rights at the global level. Special attention will be given to the role of the Human Rights Council and the Universal Periodic Review.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4 - The European system for the promotion and protection of human rights**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Chapter starts looking into the promotion and protection of human rights at regional (continental or sub-continental) levels. In particular, the European system will be presented highlighting the respective roles of the European Union, the Council of Europe, and the OSCE and their capacity to interplay and possibly complement each other.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 5 - Regional systems for the promotion and protection of human rights in Africa, Asia and the Americas**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe other regional systems investigated in this chapter are those operating in the framework of regional organisations in the Americas (the Organisation of American States), in Africa (the African Union), in the Arab world (the League of Arab States), as well as in South-East Asia (the ASEAN).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 6 - Human rights in conflict and post-conflict contexts**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe focus shifts to the national level, in particular to situations of armed conflict and to post-conflict scenarios. Issues related to the standards and procedures of International Humanitarian Law and International Criminal Law are also tackled.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 7 - Human rights promotion and protection at the National and sub-national level**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis Chapter addresses a number of issues related to the role of National Human Rights Institutions and other actors involved in human rights policies nationwide and at the local/community levels, such as local governments and municipalities.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 8 - The driving forces of human rights promotion: the role of civil society**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Chapter focuses on civil society organisations and networks. The analysis looks into the multifaceted strategies carried out by non-state actors, especially in relation to the international instances of human rights protection.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 9 - Conclusions: perspectives on global human rights**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnA summary and discussion of the multi-level dimensions of human rights protection dealt with in the previous chapters. This final segment provides some closing critical reflections on the questions set forth in Chapter 1.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Mid [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31mterm homework**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of chapter 4, the instructions for homework will be released: homework must be submitted by the end of chapter 6 (2 weeks). Homework consists of writing a communication or a petition addressed to one of the monitoring bodies studied in the first four chapters. The aim is to familiarise students with the tools of human rights protection mechanisms. The texts will be evaluated using a peer review methodology.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Final homework**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of chapter 8, the instructions for homework will be released: homework must be submitted in 2 weeks. Students will be asked to write, using a simplified form, a project addressing a human rights related issue that is challenging their town, territory, home country and likely to be taken up by governmental or non-governmental agencies.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWithin each chapter, the MOOC offers tailored case-studies, interviews with field experts, officers and academics. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately 4 hours per week for watching video lectures, taking quizzes,  completing homework and reading the material provided.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn*UNIPD*[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFounded in 1222, the University of Padova is one of Europe[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms oldest and most prestigious seats of learning: it is a multidisciplinary university, which aims to provide its students with both professional training and a solid cultural background. A qualification from the University of Padova is a symbol of having achieved an ambitious objective, one that is recognised and coveted by both students and employers alike.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf you want to know more about the University of Padova, visit its [website][2].[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn*HRC*[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Human Rights Centre of the University of Padova is the first established (in 1982) specialised structure dedicated to human rights in the framework of an Italian University, and one of the oldest in Europe. The Centre hosts the UNESCO Chair in Human rights, democracy and peace - its chair-holder being prof. Antonio Papisca - and the European Jean Monnet Centre of Excellence Intercultural dialogue, human rights and multi-level governance. It edits the Italian Yearbook of Human Rights and manages the Archive Peace Human Rights, a web portal on human rights funded by the Region of Veneto. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Centre supports the master[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms degree in Human Rights and Multi-Level Governance at the University of Padova, and the postgraduate courses of the EU-backed EIUC (the European Inter-University Centre for Human Rights and Democratisation in Venice).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLearn more about the [Human Rights Centre][1] of the University of Padova.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: http://unipd-centrodirittiumani.it/en/[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: http://www.unipd.it/en[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-01-30T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-04-03T13:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/ba83c657-bb8a-4133-ad72-4a4caabaa29c/69831620881500.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:32,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mVehicle Dynamics III: Vertical oscillations[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mFrom Bugatti Veyron to Volkswagen Beetle, from racing to passenger car: Learn how they behave on a country road and on the autobahn! [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn this third part of Vehicle Dynamics, we will illuminate the vertical dynamic aspects of vehicles. In short, we will describe the elements involved when a car drives on a bumpy or rough street.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will start with a survey of suspensions and springs and dampers. After this, we will explain the description of rough streets and give an introduction to Fourier integrals. Next, we will take a closer look at vertical models. In the last fundamental part of the course, we will describe the conflict between driving safety and comfort. The course will be finished with two applications from automotive mechatronics.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of the course you will [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA6[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - know different kinds of suspensions, springs and dampers.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - know the description of rough and bumpy streets[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the Fourier integral[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the conflict between driving safety and comfort[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - be able to calculate simple properties of a car[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSome basic understanding of the following subjects will help you successfully participate in this course: Algebra; Trigonometric Functions; Differential Calculus; Linear Algebra;  Vectors; Coordinate Systems; Force, Torque, Equilibrium; Mass, Center of Gravity, Moment of Inertia; Method of Sections, Friction, Newton's Law, (Lagrange's Equation)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - approx. 3 hours per week and exam preparation [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents participating in this course can earn the official **Statement of Participation**.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRequirements for receiving the Statement of Participation are to participate in the final exam.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-02-10T00:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-04-30T00:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/25742408-659c-47ce-8f4e-c5e9e286a2b9/70334988155600.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:380,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mFrom International Relations to Global Politics[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mFrom the theories of International Relations to the practice of global politics. To grasp the rule of the global political game and be ready to play it.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course examines the major theories of International Relations, the key sub-fields of international politics, and the current practices of global politics.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn the first part, the theories of realism, liberalism, marxism, and constructivism are studied.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn the second part, the key concepts in foreign policy analysis, internetional political economy, and security studies are presented.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn the final part, the course disentagles the context of globalization, the institutional framework of global governance, and the current reality of global politics with its risks and opportunities.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe classes will be integrated with internet hang-outs centered on current events, as well as different kinds of exercises and tests.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBy the end of the course, the student will be able to understand critically international affairs, to analyse major international events, to interpret the position of key international players, and in the ultimate analsysis to play actively the global political game.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBasic knowledge of international history and current affairs.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1 How to study International Relations (on key methodologies to study international affairs)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Structure of the course: To dos[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - How to explain international phenomena? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The Westphalian World[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The origin of the discipline: idealism[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2 Realism (on the principal paradigm of IR theory)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Anthropology and history[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Four assumptions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - State and Power[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Strategies[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Order[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Institutions and negotiations[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Geopolitics[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Justice[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Conclusions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3 Liberalism (on the second major paradigm of IR)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Introduction to liberalism[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Assumptions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Democratic Peace Theory[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Interdependence and neo-liberal institutionalism[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - International organizations and International regimes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Global governance[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Integration[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Conclusions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4 Marxism and Constructivism (on two important alternative theories)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Marxism: Class Struggle[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Four Assumptions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Teoria de la dependencia[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - World System theory[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Neo-Gramscian Approaches[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Constructivism: The power of imagination[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Ideas, identities, interests[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 5: Foreign Policy Analysis (on the first sub-field of IR)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Instruments and determinants of foreign policy[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Models of foreign policy decision-making[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 6: International Political Economy (on the second sub-field of IR)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Inequality[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The three schools of IPE[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - From the embedded liberalism to globalization[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 7: Security studies (on the third sub-field of IR)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The notion of security[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Security and strategy[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The development of war[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Models of peacebuilding[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 8: Globalization and the context of global politics (on the context of today's politics)** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What is globalization?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The future of globalization[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Conceptual maps of international affairs[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Future scenarios[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 9 Global Politics (on today's politics)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The rule of global governance[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Global politics[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Transnational civil society: nature and functions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Public institutions-civil society interaction[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The Boomerang Effect rivisited[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately 4 hours per week for watching video lectures, taking quizzes and completing homework assignments.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-02-16T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-05-04T13:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/580fa7a2-b889-4c7f-a4c0-e655c9f08d7b/70231238198700.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:224,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mMolecular Basis of Nutrition-Related Diseases[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mNutrition and health is a matter of concern to many people. Most often, we ask what kind of food is healthy or what we should avoid. But the major problem is not what we eat, the major problem is how much we eat. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOver the past decades world hunger has been joined by a second nutrition problem: chronic over nutrition and lack of exercise in industrialized and developing countries. The ensuing overweight and obesity pose a severe health problem. Picking the most relevant examples, this short course will analyze the biochemical basis of the development of diseases associated with the so called metabolic syndrome. Among others, the steps towards the development of type 2 diabetes and atherosclerosis will be discussed.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course is divided into 4 chapters. In each chapter one particular nutrition-related disease will be discussed on three levels. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevel 1: Basic understanding of how poor lifestyle impacts on the regulation of physiological processes.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevel 2: Understanding of the major biochemical principles underlying selected examples of nutrition-related diseases.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevel 3: Sound understanding, which experimental evidence supports the current views on the development of certain nutrition-related diseases.  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I need to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevel 1: Basic knowledge in biology[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevel 2: Basic knowledge of biochemical principles[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevel 3: Advanced knowledge in biochemistry[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1: Insulin Resistance.**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn You will learn, how overweight and obesity cause insulin resistance in the different organs.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2: Type 2 Diabetes.** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will learn about the current ideas, how reversible insulin resistance irreversibly proceeds to type 2 diabetes and how the late complications of type 2 diabetes develop.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3: Dyslipidemias.**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will learn, how lipids are carried in our blood and distributed throughout the body, what controls their levels and how this control is impaired in disease.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4: Atherosclerosis.**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will learn, how different risk factors, among others type 2 diabetes, dislipidemia and hypertension, contribute to the development of atherosclerosis and its consequences like stroke and heart attack. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnApproximately 2- hours per week for watching video lectures, taking quizzes and completing homework assignments.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-02-23T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-04-06T13:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mpreview[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/888f64b5-ef79-4c12-8ff5-a45dd820beb8/70062636988720.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:335,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mArchitecture 101 - Part II[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mFrom place to space: To turn a place into a space. To see spaces like architects do.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Architecture 101**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo learn more about architecture 101, we kindly invite you to read about it in the first part of the course description, [here][1]. Being this part 2 (from place to space), in order to understand the whole picture, it is better to start from [part 1][2].[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Architecture 101 (part 2: from place to space)** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn part 1 of our course, we explore the state of nothingness and start moving towards the idea of [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mplace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m. In part 2, we deal with the concept of [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mplace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m and our conceptual journey goes on towards [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mspace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**In short:**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnpart 1: from nothingness to place[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnpart 2: from place to space[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnpart 3: from space to architecture[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlaces to stay, to move, to eat, to cook, to love. Place to live. Place to die.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlaces for our bodies, places on our bodies.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlaces to clean and remember. We went all over the place... Different places for doing so many different things. Different places and different positions, all weaven to different states of mind.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOf course, in this 6-month journey called [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mArchitecture 101[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m, we expect the final output to be about making architecture. And it will be (part 3).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBut as we said before: we cannot make architecture without understanding what space is, and we cannot sense any kind of space before knowing about [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mplace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m, and we cannot imagine any kind of place without getting into a mental and physical state of pure nothingness.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**So now, how do we go from to place to space?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAs John Cage told us in the first week of part 1, [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mThere is no such thing as an empty space or an empty time. There is always something to see, something to hear. In fact, try as we may to make a silence, we cannot.[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mIn a small room one does not say what one would in a large room.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m (Louis Kahn)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**What more could we add?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn this part of the course, we will understand what kind of matter surrounds us and how this matters to us. What matters? This is what we will need to find out. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, we will try to define the boundaries of this matter at hand. Adding a new dimension to the whole thing, we will put ourselves into context. A physical and a mental context. All of this, using a [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mhands-on[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m system (you will learn by doing).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 1: taking measurements[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 2: proportions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 3: technical drawing[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 4: papercut models[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 5: the history of place / the history of space[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 6: in a world of webzines[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 7: what is an [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mexam[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 8: what is a [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mbreak[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Learning Objectives**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will see spaces like architects do.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will explore the ways in which place becomes space. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will learn to measure and project ideas into a 3 dimensional way. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will also learn a significative amount of extremely interesting (and totally useless) things.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAll of the above refers to the conceptual part of our course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, since we love having our students making practical things, you will also learn lots of technical things using a number of interesting applications.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**What will I make?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnA scale model in a box (a box with a given proportion, size, appearance) in which you will represent a specific [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mspace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m. If one thousand people finish this part 3, we will have a fabulous collection of 1000 boxes. A cool exhibition is on its way. Makes sense, don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt you think?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Prior knowledge**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis is the 2nd part of a tripartite course called Architecture 101. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo have followed the first part is highly recommended, however not required.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, in terms of other kinds of prior knowledge, nothing in particular is required. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHowever, in terms of technical equipment, this course will be easier to follow for those with access to a smartphone or tablet. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt need a smartphone or tablet. But, as we wrote, we imagined a class with thousands of people lost in their phones, from all around the world. In commuters, we trust![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBetween 3 and 7 hours a week. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFrom Monday to Friday, for a total of 6 weeks, you will receive an email with a 15 second-video to watch (to get you in the mood), and a pdf with some instructions for completing an assignment and a series of references (to go deeper in the subject at hand).  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, you will get to work on your assignment. Once you complete your assignment, you will upload it to the iversity platform and share it on your preferred social media account(s). Ideally Instagram. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, during the weekend, we will give you some time to catch up.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAre you ready?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn:-)  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://iversity.org/de/courses/architecture-101-part-i[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://iversity.org/de/courses/architecture-101-part-i[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-03-02T13:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-04-25T13:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/e455f0ed-813a-4086-896d-8a066d8fa756/70206255302480.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:362,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mArchitecture 101 - Part III[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mFrom space to architecture: To structure, order and transform space into architecture. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Architecture 101**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo learn more about architecture 101, we kindly invite you to read about it in the first part of the course description, [here][1]. Eventually, also read the description of part 2 [here][2].[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Architecture 101 (part 3: from space to architecture)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn part 1 of our course, we explore the state of nothingness and start to understand the idea of [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mplace[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m. In part 2 we learn to transform a place into a space. Now, we are ready for part 3: to transform a space into architecture. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**What does it mean to transform a space into architecture?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mArchitecture is the thoughtful making of space.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m Louis Kahn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn part 2, we learn that space is composed of mind and matter. Now, in order for us to benefit from this matter, we need to put it in order. And this is exactly what architecture is all about. Architecture is about giving a very specific kind of meaning and symbolic value to a series of different things. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn this part of the course, we will plan, design and construct a system in which to organize and render coherent important matter (that matters to us). A matter of structure and proportions.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBy doing so, we will give a new sense to place and space.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Are you ready?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur 6-month online journey will be celebrated at Abadir in Sicily, where we will set up our final exhibition. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 1: materials[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 2: colors[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 3: sounds[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 4: moving images[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 5: animations[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 6: the video[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 7: about the exam[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 8: break / exhibition / graduation party at Abadir, in Sicily[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek extra: Architecture 101 Summer Camp at Abadir, in Sicily (where we will build for real). If you are still alive by then, this [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mphysical[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m 5-day workshop is a course in itself and it will soon be officially announced.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo see architecture like architects do.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo explore the ways in which space becomes architecture. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo learn that form follows fiction. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe will also learn a significative amount of extremely interesting (and totally useless) things.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAll of the above refers to the conceptual part of our course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, since we love having our students making practical things, you will also learn lots of technical things using a number of interesting applications.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**At the end, what do I make?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnA video (with a given set of constraints) in which you will show your built 1 to 1 architecture. If one thousand people finish this part 3, we will have a fabulous collection of 1000 videos representing 1000 architectural concepts.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Prior knowledge**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis is the 3rd part of a tripartite course called Architecture 101. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo have followed the first 2 parts (1 + 2) is highly recommended, however not required.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, in terms of other kinds of prior knowledge, nothing in particular is required. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHowever, in terms of technical equipment, this course will be easier to follow for those with access to a smartphone or tablet. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt need a smartphone or tablet. But, as we wrote, we imagined a class with thousands of people lost in their phones, from all around the world. In commuters, we trust![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBetween 3 and 7 hours a week. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFrom Monday to Friday, for a total of 6 weeks, you will receive an email with a 15 second-video to watch (to get you in the mood), and a pdf with some instructions for completing an assignment and a series of references (to go deeper in the subject at hand).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, you will get to work on your assignment. Once you complete your assignment, you will upload it to the iversity platform and share it on your preferred social media account(s). Ideally Instagram.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, during the weekend, we will give you some time to catch up.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAre you ready?  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn:-)  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://iversity.org/de/courses/architecture-101-part-i[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://iversity.org/de/courses/architecture-101-part-ii[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-04-27T00:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2015-06-27T00:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mannounced[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/e185fdcf-8d4b-4b15-b513-39457dc1e867/70226903019100.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:287,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mPolitical Philosophy: An Introduction[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mAre you interested in politics? Do you feel the need to have a clearer understanding of it, beyond the conventional language of media and social networks? Well, this course might provide the help and the stimulus you are looking for.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course is designed as a vocabulary of the main terms used by all of us when talking about local as well as world politics; terms which we often use without a proper awareness of their meanings and connections, a circumstance not exactly helpful to any attempt at understanding how politics really works, regardless of our wishful thinking or simplistic morality or easy cynicism.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNow, if we want to get deeper into the workings of politics - the only serious starting point for those who want to reform it - we must agree to begin with very abstract notions, that is with the general definitions of what politics, conflict, power (incl. force/violence), and what legitimate power mean (Part 1: What is Politics?). On these premises we will then explain the still main political institution, the state, and peer into the dynamics of war and peace that has dominated the relationships between the states (Part 2: How Does Politics Work?). Since with economic globalization, which has restricted the room for political action, things are getting much more complicated on the planet, and more challenging outside of it (man-made climate change starts in the atmosphere),  classical notions have to be rethought. The very nature of the threats endangering our global commons does not leave the definition of politics  (Part 3: World Politics and the Future).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course does not aim at communicating any 'message' as to how politics ought to be, but it will obviously try to clarify the main concepts - freedom, equality, justice -  we make use of while talking about values and principles in politics; this is what is called  'normative political philosophy' and is regarded here as an important chapter of political philosophy, not the whole of it (Part 4: Ethics and Politics).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of the course you may have achieved a clearer and less confused awareness of the political vocabulary, thus gaining a more complex, more autonomous and more critical understanding of political processes. If you are a student of political science, law, sociology and economics you may get better tools for catching the overarching sense of processes that you do otherwise approach in a fragmented perspective.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDue to my conceptual approach, to follow this course you do not need a prior knowledge of philosophy or political science, just the degree of general culture needed to pass the final high school exam, be it Abitur, maturit[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA0[0m[31m, baccalaur[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA9[0m[31mat or [1;35m\xE9[0m[31m[1;35m\xAB[0m[31m[1;35m\x98[0m[31m[1;35m\xE8[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x83[0m[31m(gao kao).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Course Structure**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn| **Chapter**  | [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;**Topic**  |[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn| :--------------------------- |:------------------------------------------------------- [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn| Chapter 1|[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;    Aim and method of the course. General information. Two definitions of politics. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn| Chapter 2|[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;   Disassembling the classical definition, and its components: Conflict, (Legitimate) Power, Force.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn| Chapter 3|[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026nbsp;[1;35m\\[0m[