or those who already have an idea for a start-up and want to learn from seasoned experts about all the areas you need to think of before starting-up. Muhammad Yunus, Scilla Elworthy, Jean-Remy von Matt and 34 other leaders share their secrets to success in the DO School Start-Up Lab.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStop wondering, start DOing![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**When does the course start?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will go live with chapter 1 on the 28th June 2014 at 3.45 pm (GMT+1). Chapter 2 will be activated on the 8th July and from then on another chapter on Tuesday every week until the final chapter opens on the 26th August, 2014.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Have a clear idea about the societal relevance and value added by their venture and a plan for maximizing their social impact[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Have consolidated the project and resource planning for their venture[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Have developed their revenue model and financing strategy and taken first steps to fundraising for their venture[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Have defined their legal and organizational requirements and taken the first steps towards the set-up of their organization[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Have defined their human resource strategy and needs and taken action to meet them[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Know what is unique about their venture and how they communicate it to their target groups[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo specific skills are required other than passion for an issue or opportunity that you want to address for the better of your society. However, this course is ideal for people who already have a concrete start-up idea as it supports the actual implementation of relevant first steps in implementing such an idea. It doesn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt matter whether you want to create a not-for-profit or for-profit venture.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf you don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt have a concrete idea yet, the course will be valuable to distill your idea and find out about what it takes to start-up successfully.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf you really work on implementing your venture idea, we expect you to commit at least 12 hours a week in order to complete the course materials, make use of the worksheets and do the necessary research and work to start implementing your venture. If you just take the course as a primer and because you think about starting something up soon, you will need about 3-4 hours minimum per week. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents can earn the official Statement of Participation by completing at least 80% of the course requirements.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![enter image description here][1] ![enter image description here][2][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://iversity.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/image-uploads/6125-aedeb2b84f9b15e157ec7aea9afa2da5_thumb.jpg[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://iversity.s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/image-uploads/6125-a7e275ba29942bb5e7bdd7b8b6ae6f5a_thumb.png[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-06-27T10:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-08-31T18:42:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/232b1518-cae5-4dee-b262-b6a9285a5b50/70056630660320.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:13,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mModelling and Simulation using MATLAB[1;35m\xC2[0m[31m[1;35m\xAE[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mHow can I simulate a water treatment plant or realise a new business venture? This MOOC explains how to model and simulate innovative ideas using MATLAB/Simulink. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnModelling and simulation make a particular part of the world easier to define, visualize and understand. Both require the identification of relevant aspects of a situation in the real world and then the use of different types of models for different objectives and the definition of the most suitable model parameters.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course teaches you to simulate models for a wide range of applications using MATLAB [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m a high-level programming language and an environment for numerical computation and visualization.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Students are acquainted with the concepts of modelling and simulation from an interdisciplinary point of view.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Students are able to implement and simulate models using MATLAB/Simulink.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Depending on the selected applications in part B of the course students acquire further knowledge of control engineering, image processing, machine learning, business case modelling, knowledge management and simulation of a water treatment plant[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Enthusiastic students with only rudimentary programming knowledge acquire an understanding of the basic MATLAB programming[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnMathematics and Physics knowledge of secondary level education and programming knowledge are recommended. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnMATLAB is commercial software. As a result of support from MathWorks, students will be granted a downloadable license to MATLAB and Simulink for the duration of the course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn Approx. 8 hours per week.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe final chapter will be uploaded on July 8th. The course ends on August 1st.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents participating in this course can earn the official **Statement of Participation**.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRequirements for receiving the Statement of Participation are to watch 60% of the lecture videos as well as complete 60% of the quizzes. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-22T11:59:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-08-11T21:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/0b9e1cb7-16e3-4cd3-bc27-76cfab441eb7/70308638464160.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:50,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mGamification Design Online Course[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDo you want to know what Gamification really is about? Do you want to learn how to design fun and engaging experiences? Are you ready to change your world with game design? Then join us in this MOOC! [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m### Why Gamification?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnGames have become the new normal. The gaming industry is already more powerful than other ways of entertainment like music or movies. An average young person will spend more than 10,000 hours gaming by the age of 21 - somewhat the time that it takes us to master any kind of skill- and yet, there's a huge engagement crisis in many other areas. 70% of US full-time employees are not motivated by what they are doing, kids spend way more time engaged with video games than they do with books, the average attention span in 2012 was less than 10 seconds and it's decreasing every year...[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIt seems like only games are truly understanding how human motivation really works. But how is that possible? Why are we glued to games? Can we design that kind of gameful experiences in non-game contexts to make them more engaging?   [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAnd the most important question: How to do so?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Course Structure[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 1** (17/03/2014) Games. Game Design. Gamefulness. Gamification[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 2** (31/03/2014) Psychology and Gamification: Why are games and gamification so engaging?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 3** (07/04/2014)The different types of Gamification [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 4** (14/04/2014) Defining gamified experiences: Things to know before we start[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 5** (21/04/2014) Creating gamified experiences: The first steps of the design process[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 6** (28/04/2014) Designing gamified experiences: Storytelling, mechanics, aesthetics and much more[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Week 7** (05/05/2014) Going further than the basics[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Learning Outcomes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn this course you'll learn the basics of Gamification with a highly practical approach. We'll especially focus on how to design gamified experiences in real life and students will be able to gain knowledge in areas such as: game design, psychology, management, or education. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur main goal will be to understand and master the principles of gamification to design experiences that make things more fun and engaging.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Who is this course for?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDo you want your team to perfom better? Are you looking for ways to fully engage happy customers? Do you want to see kids learning while playing? Or are you just looking forward to seeing a better world? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnGamification can be used in many areas and almost any task can be fun and engaging so this course could be great for people like: teachers, educators, managers, C-level executives, health and fitness professionals, psychologists or researchers. So...[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhether you ever asked yourself one of these questions or you just want to know how to make things more fun and engaging, this course is for you![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Prior Knowledge[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis is a level 1 course and all you need to bring in the class is a playful attitude! Anyway, having some prior knowledge is always great, so if you already want to start this epic adventure, here are 3 ways you can do so:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- If you want to start reading some books on it: http://www.epicwinblog.net/2013/05/best-gamification-books-where-to-start.html[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- If you[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31md rather learn by doing: http://www.epicwinblog.net/2013/10/the-35-gamification-mechanics-toolkit.html[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- And if you like none of them, well, there[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms always a way. Go and start playing games! [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Assessments and Certification[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis MOOC will be based on creative assignments where we[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll try you to learn by doing and after successfully completing those assignments, students will receive their statement certificates of accomplishment if their overall score is higher than 7. Besides, everyone will receive an statement of participation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Workload[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course will feature weekly videos and creative assignments so you[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll have to spend around 3-4 hours per week, and if you want to know more, we[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll provide you with reading references and plenty of insightful videos, blogs and resources. In addition, there will be live hangouts and local meetups so the workload is actually up to you.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Live G+ Hangouts [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Local Meetups[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe plan to do Live Hangouts with the best students of the week, and local meetups with the best communities of the course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Live Hangouts**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnEvery 2-3 weeks, we[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll ask all the students to discuss about some interesting topics and we'll feature the most insightful ones on a weekly hangout. More information coming soon.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Local Meetups**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll foster local communities within the course and we[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll try to organise meetups with the biggest and most active ones from all over the world. To do so, we[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll select 3 organisers that voluntarily apply for that position in the forums and then try to coordinate a meetup with the teachers during the course or afterwards. Stay tuned for more exciting news![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Keep in touch![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe are quite active on FB, Twitter, G+ and blogs! You can follow us and engage in the conversation here:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Facebook:** [Gamification Design MOOC Page][1][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Twitter:** **#GDMooc** [@victormanriquey][2] / [@isidrorodrigo][3] / [@kokopus_dark][4] [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Linkedin:** [Gamification Design MOOC Network][6][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Google+:** [Gamification Design MOOC G+ and Live Hangouts Community][7][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Our Blogs:** [Epic Win Blog][8] / [HR Gamer][9] [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Official #GDMooc Student Communities[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Facebook**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn-  [Gamification Group][10][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### FAQ[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at Iversity's [FAQ][11] if you have any other questions regarding the platform.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://www.facebook.com/GamificationDesignMOOC?ref=hl[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: http://twitter.com/victormanriquey[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [3]: http://twitter.com/isidrorodrigo[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [4]: http://twitter.com/kokopus_dark[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [5]: http://twitter.com/McEwan22[1