mnClear and brief: acceleration and braking. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn Detail: After an introduction, we will look at driving resistances and slip, explain the demand of power and limits of a car, then clarify the needs for a clutch and gears and look at the rear and front weights during acceleration and braking. The course will be finished by two applications from automotive mechatronics.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBy the end of the course you will [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA6[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand basic principles of accelerating and braking a car.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - know the driving resistances and their influences on vehicle dynamics.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the discrepancy between demands and limits of powertrain.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the necessity of gears and clutch.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the correlation between braking, wheel load and recovery of energy. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - be able to calculate simple properties of a car.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSome basic understanding  of the following subjects will help you successfully participate in this course: Algebra; Trigonometric Functions; Differential Calculus; Linear Algebra;  Vectors; Coordinate Systems; Force, Torque, Equilibrium; Mass, Center of Gravity, Moment of Inertia; Method of Sections, Friction, Newton's Law, (Lagrange's Equation)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn Approx. 3 hours per week and exam preparation [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents participating in this course can earn the official **Statement of Participation**.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRequirements for receiving the Statement of Participation are to participate in the final exam.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-15T11:30:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-07-22T00:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/cec79779-1406-4eb2-a38c-ef858415b368/79487180.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:10,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDNA - From Structure to Therapy[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDNA stores our genetic information and many diseases are caused by changes in its sequences. We will first learn about the basics of DNA and then find out how it allows for the development of diagnostic and therapeutic strategies.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDNA is a molecule that we all encounter every day, one way or the other, often without knowing: We inherit traits from our parents encoded in DNA, diagnostics and forensics (as featured in TV serials like CSI) are often based on DNA, and many incurable diseases are caused by changes in DNA sequences. Based on milestone experiments, using models and whiteboard sequences, we want to convey our fascination for DNA and provide you with basic knowledge of DNA structure and function to better understand biomedical approaches for diagnostics and therapy. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnParticipants will be able to answer the following questions after completing the course:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Why and how has DNA become one of the most powerful tools in research?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - How does DNA look and why is DNA structure so important?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - What do the terms cell division, mitosis, transcription, translation and mutation mean?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - Why is it so hard to find a cure for cancer?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - For which diseases is DNA technology used as a diagnostic tool?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - For which diseases may DNA-based technology help developing a therapy?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn order to follow our course, basic high school biology and chemistry knowledge is absolutely sufficient. In order to successfully complete all homework assignments, including more in depth questions, you will need some more time and motivation to read further and catch up on certain topics. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - 2 hours per week for watching videos [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 taking quizzes [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - 2-4 hours for completing homework assignments, depending on your prior knowledge (voluntary)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents participating in this course can earn the official **Statement of Participation** for free.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRequirement for receiving the Statement of Participation is minimum progress (80% participation in videos and quizzes).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnHomework assignments will help you to further increase your understanding but are not required for the certificate.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Facebook**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur course has a [facebook page][1]. Come join us there too![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://www.facebook.com/jubmooc[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-25T11:53:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-06-30T18:24:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/00e09113-236d-44d2-bbf3-94a788d8c37a/79472020.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:25,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDark Matter in Galaxies: The Last Mystery[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mThere is something out there in space, something invisible we have a hard time to understand. But we can be certain of one thing: It played a major role in the formation of our and any other galaxy![1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mStudy a Phenomenon, that does not (yet) have an explanation. Challenge the universe and use recent observations and smart techniques to get through the veil of this phenomenon. Becomhttps://iversity.org/my/courses/dark-matter-in-galaxies-the-last-mystery/edit#e part of the generation of scientists that will unveil this 80 years old mystery or be among those who will witness that occurring. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Structure[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 1: The evidence of the phenomenon[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 2: Galaxies [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 3 : Introduction to Dark Matter [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 4: Measuring the Universe[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 5: Entering the issue[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 6: The gravitational potential of galaxies[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 7: Dark matter halos[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 8: The essence of the DM phenomenon [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 9: Mass modelling galaxies [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 10: A deeper analysis on Dark Matter[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 11: The Stellar properties of galaxies[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 12: Conclusions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Format[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course has three teaching modes. The knowledge is transferred through 1) documentary style videos 2) records of front lectures delivered by the teacher(s) and enhanced by useful extra information installed in them  in a post-production phase 3) animations of formulae, plots and simulations. The videos will be in Italian with English subtitles. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnQuizzes allow the students to receive feedback on their understanding and in the forums the students can interact, ask questions and discuss the learnings. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Learning Outcomes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLevels of the course are Advanced, Regular, Basic.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Students, in general, will learn an important and strategic subject of Astrophysics and Physics, at university level and will be able to successfully teach it at high school level.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Advanced students will be able to get deep inside into the complex field of Dark Matter in Galaxies from one of the leading scientist in the field. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Enthusiastic outsiders with only simple knowledge of Physics and Mathematics can enter one the biggest mysteries of nature and get an understanding of the topic which allows them to follow its revelation. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Workload[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe time needed to complete the requirements: [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Watching videos ~10 hours [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Practical work  5-15 hours [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Self-study  work  5-15 hours[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Projects 0-15 hours [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Assessments 5-10 hours[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Assessments[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe  assessments of the  course employs: multiple choices tests and peer review of projects. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###FAQ[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at the [FAQ][1] if you have any general questions regarding the platform.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1]: https://www.iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2013-10-15T10:51:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-06-30T10:51:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/f3d9d4b3-ac9f-42e2-beb8-8cc2f755b606/79491580.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:4,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mThe Fascination of Crystals and Symmetry[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mRubies, sugar, snowflakes: crystals are beauty, arranged in grid structures. This MOOC explains the basic building blocks of crystals, their symmetrical structure and introduces free software for crystal structure exploring.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn this course,  we will provide you with a basic introduction into crystallography. The focus is placed upon the symmetry elements, which occur in crystals. The arrangement of the atoms inside the crystal needs a more detailed description than the overall shape of the crystal (morphology). We want to show you how symmetry is classified in a hierarchical way. We want our students to gain the ability to discover symmetry on their own.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of the course you will ...[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - be aware of the similarities between the patterns on wallpaper and the structures of crystals.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - be able to classify the innumerable appearances of crystals into the seven different crystal systems.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - know how to find crystallographic data and how to analyze it regarding symmetry.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the description of infinite framework structures (i.e. MOFs) via a topology approach.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand  the relationship between the structure and the properties of a material. Ex.: Why is diamond so hard and the explanation of phenomena such as ferroelectricity?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBasic knowledge in chemistry (atoms, simple molecules). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - approx. 3 hours per week[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents participating in this course can earn the official *Statement of Participation*. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRequirements for receiving the Statement of Participation are to watch 80% of the lecture videos as well as complete 80% of the quizzes. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-22T11:59:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-06-20T17:30:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/f872ebfa-83ee-4c56-8671-fbca0344563f/79477300.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:87,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDesign Thinking Online Course[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mWhether you are a student, a designer or an entrepreneur, join this course and develop your creativity methods and innovation attitude while exploring the human-centred design-approach.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn#### **Welcome to the Macromedia University Design Thinking MOOC.**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe first Macromedia University MOOC Design Thinking is about understanding and implementing the methodology of Design Thinking. You will learn how Design Thinking uses creative, human centered techniques as a strategic approach to stimulate innovation. At MHMK, Macromedia University of Applied Sciences, we believe that human needs and experience should drive innovation [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m not technology. Being a school whose graduates will engage in designing the digital landscape surrounding us, we like to share our conviction of a good, decent and ethical way of creating tomorrows products and services. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Sign up now! The four-week-MOOC starts 14 April 2014 and ends 12 May 2014.** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What to Expect**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe Macromedia MOOC Design Thinking links theoretical frames with practice. You will look into fundamentals like historical and theoretical aspects of design, design models and design systems. You will gain deeper insights into the Design Thinking methodology and the human-centered design approach. You will learn how to apply teamwork and communications skills, and you will hear about creativity methods and visualization tools in the context of strategic design. And last but not least, the Macromedia MOOC Design Thinking will teach you how to evaluate ideas and concepts and why an innovation attitude and intercultural communication competence is crucial for a successful implementation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek by week we invite you to meet academics, professionals and students, who are using Design Thinking in the creative industries as well as in management in order to solve problems of great complexity.  Each week is divided into three or four lectures/chapters. Each lecture is divided in several lessons/units, which are usually not longer than 5 mInutes. The lessons are made of video material, slides, additional reading material and tasks.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Expect to view approx. 80 minutes of lectures per week which sums up to altogether 5 hours per week incl. self-study time.**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###**Email Contact for Course Related Questions:**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003Ca href=[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mmailto:mooc@macromedia.de[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003E[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003E mooc@macromedia.de[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003C/a[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003E[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Why this MOOC is interdisciplinary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOriginating in the Design Department of MHMK, Macromedia University of Applied Sciences in Munich, the Macromedia MOOC Design Thinking is emphasizing the rewarding link between management and creativity. To us, managing creativity means drawing on various findings and multidiscliplinary methods, yet guiding them through standardized and verifiable management procedures. Besides Design and Art history, the background of our MOOC team therefore ranges from business, psychology and human resource to transmedia, visualization, narration, and journalism, for instance. We will thus be able to discuss Design Thinking from various perspectives.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Learning Outcomes**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn***Our MOOC will help you answer the following questions:***[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn1. What is Design Thinking? Which benefits may I expect when implementing it as a management strategy? [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m2. How can innovation be systematically  triggered ?[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m How can I implement Design Thinking into my own projects? 3. Talking about the potential of Design Thinking [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m what kind of best practices are there ? [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m4. What kind of team do I need to in order to initialize a Design Thinking process?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Prior Knowledge**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo prior knowledge of Design Thinking is needed in order to attend the MOOC. [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31mInterest in creative techniques, innovation and management is welcome.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m- You don't know what human centered design, strategic design or participatory innovation culture is? - Great, you'll learn it here.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA8[0m[31m- You are a business development specialist? - Great, we hope to inspire you. Please feel free to help us inspire others by sharing interesting links, events and projects on our Facebook page.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![Join the Macromedia University Network][1][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###[[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003E Click here if you wish to subscribe to the news and update service of Macromedia University][2][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWe would be happy to keep you posted![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----------[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn![enter image description here][3][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###[**[1;35m\\[0m[31mu003E Click here to link to the Fan Page on Facebook:**][4] [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBecome a friend and follow the conversation! [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://iversity.s3.amazonaws.com/image-uploads/1052802-68cf63230a37b7a1d805b964380c601a_thumb.jpg[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: http://www.macromedia-fachhochschule.de/mooc[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [3]: https://iversity.s3.amazonaws.com/image-uploads/1052802-84468aff0afadc9d72de5441bded227b_thumb.png[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [4]: https://www.facebook.com/MacromediaMOOC[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-14T08:14:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-06-19T17:58:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/b038a80a-7b03-46bd-9915-b06378a2a1a9/69822885243040.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:7,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mThe European Union in Global Governance[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mWhat are the challenges the EU faces, and can it rise to meet them? Sign up and learn more about the EU as a global actor and its role in the international, political, economic, environmental and security arena.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Course Summary**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe study of the EU as an international actor has become a key element in European and International Law, European Studies and International Relations. The EU represents the world[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms largest trade power and aid donor, has a diplomatic service larger than that of most states, and has launched more than 20 civil-military operations. It has presented itself as a normative, global actor, and its emergence as a legal entity that is neither a state nor a classic international organization has both puzzled and fascinated legal scholars and political scientists alike. We represent a consortium consisting of the Global Governance Programme of the European University Institute in Florence, the Leuven Centre for Global Governance Studies and the Chair for European and International Economic Law at the University of Passau. We have joined forces guided by the vision of providing cutting-edge expertise on the many facets of this fast-evolving topic to the greatest number of students.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What will I learn?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of the course you will [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA6[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - be able to identify and understand the main challenges of the EU and its Member States in the world today, and how they affect us personally[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand the means which the EU has at its disposal to tackle these challenges, and learn ways to critically evaluate its performance.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - understand and be able to apply the key legal principles and political realities governing EU external relations, its relationship with its Member States and citizens, and the outside world.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - situate the EU as an international actor into the main theoretical approaches to International Relations, and harness these approaches to analyze current topics in global politics.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**What do I have to know?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBasic knowledge in one or more of the following subjects is highly recommended:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - The EU and its institutions / EU politics[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - EU / International law[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - International relations / politics, foreign policy.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Line-up of contributors**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Geert de Baere**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAssistant Professor of International Law and EU Law at the Faculty of Law and Senior Member of the Leuven Centre for Global Governance Studies, KU Leuven. From 2007 to 2009, worked as a r[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA9[0m[31mf[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA9[0m[31mrendaire at the Court of Justice of the EU. Author of *Constitutional Principles of EU External Relations* (Oxford University Press 2008).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Marise Cremona**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProfessor of European Law at the EUI Law Department. Between 2009 and June 2012 Head of the Law Department and between June 2012 and August 2013 President ad interim of the EUI. Co-Director of the Academy of European Law. Member of the Governing Board of the Istituto Affari Internazionali, Rome; member of the International Advisory Board of the Centre for European Research, University of G[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xB6[0m[31mteborg, Sweden; member of the Advisory Board of the European Foreign Affairs Review; member of the Editorial Board of the European Law Review.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Giorgia Giovannetti**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProfessor of Economics at the University of Florence and Visiting Fellow at the European University Institute. Scientific Director of the European Report on Development in 2009 and 2010 and former Director of the Research Centre of the Italian Trade Institute (2005-2007). Advising the Italian Treasury and Ministry of Foreign Trade since 2002. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Christoph Herrmann**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProfessor of European and International Economic Law at the University of Passau. His research focuses on the relationship between the EU and the international economic legal order, in particular EU trade policy as well as the Eurozone and its relations with the IMF and other international actors. Editor of the European Yearbook of International Economic Law (EYIEL), listed on the indicative list of panelists of the WTO and was the case author of the ELSA EMC2 WTO Law Moot Court (2012/13). Author of several monographs and textbooks on EU law and international trade law.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Jo[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xAB[0m[31mlle Hivonnet**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnEuropean External Acrion Service (EEAS), China Division, where she is contributing to the implementation of the EU-China strategic partnership. European Official since 1992. Worked previously in Brussels, New York and Geneva. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Frank Hoffmeister**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDeputy Head of Cabinet in Commissioner De Gucht[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms Cabinet (international trade). Formerly member of the External Relation Team at the European Commission[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms Legal Service. Part- time Professor at the Vrije Universiteit Brussels for International Economic Law.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Stephan Keukeleire** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJean Monnet Professor in European Integration and EU Foreign Policy, University of Leuven and Visiting Professor at the College of Europe (Bruges), Belgium. Director of the 'Master in European Studies: Transnational and Global Perspectives' at the University of Leuven. His theoretical research focuses on the analysis of foreign policy in an era of globalisation, with the concept of 'structural foreign policy' being at the heart of his research. Coordinator of the Online Resource Guide Exploring EU Foreign Policy: www.eufp.eu. Co-author of the The Foreign Policy of the European Union (Palgrave Macmillan 2014). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Joris Larik**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAcademic coordinator of the MOOC on *The EU in Global Governance* and senior researcher at the Leuven Centre for Global Governance Studies, KU Leuven. His research focuses on the law of external relations of the European Union, comparative [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 multilevel constitutional law and comparative regional integration. Winner of the NATO Manfred W[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xB6[0m[31mrner Essay Award 2008. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Liu Lei**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJean-Monnet postdoctoral fellow at the Global Governance Programme of the EUI. Currently working on the allocation of embodied emissions in international trade against the backdrop of the controversy over the production or consumption-based emissions inventory in current climate regime. His past research experiences include policy design for local environmental governance in Shenzhen and Yunnan of China, investigation of CO2 emissions embodied in China[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms industrial sectors and foreign trade, low-carbon transition of China and the global climate governance strategy.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Frederik Naert**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnMember of the Legal Service of the Council of the European Union (external relations directorate) and Affiliated Senior Researcher at the Institute for International Law, KU Leuven. Editor-in-Chief of the Military Law [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Law of War Review / Revue de droit militaire et de droit de la guerre and a member of the Board of Directors of the International Society for Military Law [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Law of War. Author of *International Law Aspects of the EU[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms Security and Defence Policy, with a Particular Focus on the Law of Armed Conflict and Human Rights* (Intersentia 2009).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Timea Pal**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJean Monnet postdoctoral fellow at the Global Governance Programme of the EUI. She is also part of the Climate Policy Research Unit (CPRU), a research group within the EUI[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms  Robert Schuman Centre for Advanced Studies (RSCAS) under the Loyola de Palacio Chair. She is a political economist working on the governance of global production chains, and on its implications on sustainable economic development in emerging economies. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Roman Petrov**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJean Monnet Chair in EU Law at the Kyiv-Mohyla Academy since 2010. Lectured the very first Jean Monnet Module in EU law in Ukraine at the Donetsk National University. Former Max Weber Fellow at the EUI. Author of one of the first Ukrainian textbooks on EU Law. Founder and first elected President of the Ukrainian European Studies Association. Frequently provides consultancy to state institutions in Ukraine, including the Constitutional Court of Ukraine and Ministry of Justice.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Kolja Raube** [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSenior Researcher, Leuven Centre for Global Governance Studies and Programme Coordinator, Centre for European Studies, KU Leuven. Heads the interdisciplinary research project *The Rule of Law [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m A Strategic Priority of the European Union[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms External Action*. Author of *Die Verfassungsau[1;35m\xCE[0m[31m[1;35m\xB2[0m[31menpolitik der Europ[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA4[0m[31mischen Union (The constitutional foreign policy of the Europrean Union)* (Nomos 2007). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Anna Triandafyllidou**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProfessor at the Global Governance Programme (GGP) of the Robert Schuman Centre for Advanced Studies (RSCAS), EUI and Director of the Programme Research Strand on [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mCultural Pluralism[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m. Her main areas of research and teaching are cultural diversity, migration, and nationalism from a European and international perspective. For the last 10 years, she has received funding and co-ordinated a number of international research projects in these research areas. Her publications include more than 100 articles in refereed journals and chapters in collective volumes, five authored books and more than ten edited and co-edited volumes, including *Irregular Migration in Europe: Myths and Realities* (Ashgate 2010) and *What is Europe?* (with R. Gropas, Palgrave 2014).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Jan Wouters**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDirector of the Leuven Centre for Global Governance Studies, Professor of International Law and International Organizations, and Jean Monnet Chair ad personam EU and Global Governance, KU Leuven. Visiting Professor at Sciences Po (Paris) and the College of Europe (Bruges). Inter alia, President of the United Nations Association Flanders Belgium, Of Counsel at Linklaters, Brussels,  Member of the Royal Flemish Academy of Belgium for Sciences and Arts. Editor of the International Encyclopedia of Intergovernmental Organizations, Deputy Director of the Revue belge de droit international and an editorial board member in ten international journals. Widely published on international, EU, corporate and financial law (over 500 publications including 46 books and 90 international journal articles).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Workload**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn 4 hours per week including readings, watching our videos, discuss with fellow students, complete quizzes.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn####**Do I get a certificate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents participating in this course can earn the official Statement of Participation.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRequirements for receiving the Statement of Participation are to watch 80% of the lecture videos as well as complete 80% of the quizzes.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-22T11:59:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-06-13T18:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/93e40d01-984a-4cbb-be8e-07337c498913/70330154980060.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:19,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mWeb Engineering II: Developing Mobile HTML5 Apps[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mLearn how to design and develop a mobile Web app. What about realising a real-time multi-player game? We show you the way to get your idea to the app store.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mBecome familiar with the challenges that come with the planning, development, testing, and maintenance of HTML5 apps. Web Engineering takes you through the concepts, methods, techniques, and tools needed for systematically developing websites and Web applications. In Web Engineering I [[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mBasics of Web Development[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m] [1] we learned how to create a professional website, and now we take a step further as you develop your very own HTML5 app![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUsing the HTML5 mobile application framework Sencha Touch, you will go online and practice handling the infrastructure and tools needed for the development and maintenance of an established Web app. In particular, you will learn the basic technical and architectural principles necessary for Web app building.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Content[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeb Engineering II builds upon on the material learned in the first course, [Web Engineering I] [2].[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnEach chapter presents the following content through a series of instructional videos, screencasts and online interactive exercises. You will also work in small groups, applying and testing practical examples of key technical aspects in Web development.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 11: Starter Kit: Tools for the HTML5 App in the Cloud [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 12: REST Architectural Style for Mobile Web Applications[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 13: Interactive Exercises with JavaScript at Codecademy[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 14: Single-Page Applications with AJAX, JSON, and REST APIs[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 15: Overview of HTML5 and its JavaScript APIs[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 16: Exercises with the HTML5 Mobile Application Framework Sencha Touch [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 17: Introduction to NoSQL Databases for Web Apps[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 18: Full-Stack JavaScript: Design and Implementation of a WebSocket App[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 19: Preparing an HTML5 App for App Stores[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Chapter 20: Screen Casting Web Apps for User Documentation[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAs a learning object for exploring and applying the course content, we will use the mobile Web-based Audience-Response System [ARSnova][3]. It will be used as a live feedback app throughout the MOOC. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Course Language[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe official course language is English, but the videos will be in German with English subtitles and slides. This is due to the fact that the course is part of the THM curriculum of Computer Science for German students.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Course Structure[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe entire course consists of two consecutive parts: the [first part of the course Web Engineering I] [4], started on 15 October 2013, and this course, Web Engineering II, started on 17 January 2014. Each course consists of 10 chapters with 6 to 8 learning units and has a weekly workload time of about 6 hours. For students at universities, the entire course has a workload equivalent to 6 ECTS credits.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn*With sufficient prior knowledge, you can move directly onto Web Engineering II.*[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Learning Objectives[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of the two-part course, you will be able to:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn 1. Develop a high-performance, secure and accessible website, upon a client[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms request. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn 2. Design and realise an HTML5 app and upload this to app stores.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Who is this course aimed at?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBoth parts of the MOOC [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mWeb Engineering[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m are aimed at undergraduate students of computer science, including media and business computer science, computer science specialist trainees in the field of application development, and working Web designers. For students of THM in the Department of MNI, the entire MOOC [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mWeb Engineering[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m is equivalent to the Bachelor module [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mInternet-Based Systems[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m (CS 1024).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Prerequisites for Course Participation[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou must have a working knowledge of HTML/CSS as provided by the track [Web Fundamentals][5] from Codecademy. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Course Certificates[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will receive a certificate for both Web Engineering I and II, if you provide the following:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Web Engineering I: completion of the online final exam and creation of a website[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Web Engineering II: completion of the online final exam and creation of an HTML5 App[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn### Our Experience[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWhoever offers an online course in Web engineering should be able to offer appropriate references as well. In recent years, we have worked in the areas of e-learning and Web-based systems. This includes the university search engine Pharus, the learning and collaboration platform eCollab, and the mobile Audience-Response System ARSnova. These were developed as open source student projects, starting from bachelor and master projects to production.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLooking back, it was the course [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mWeb Engineering[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m that adequately prepared students for these developing projects. If you complete both parts of the course Web Engineering I and II, you will be able to do the same.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###FAQ[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at the [FAQ][6] if you have any general questions regarding iversity courses.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://iversity.org/courses/web-engineering-i-grundlagen-der-web-entwicklung[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://iversity.org/courses/web-engineering-i-grundlagen-der-web-entwicklung[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [3]: https://arsnova.eu/blog/[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [4]: https://iversity.org/courses/web-engineering-i-grundlagen-der-web-entwicklung[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [5]: http://www.codecademy.com/de/tracks/web[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [6]: https://iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-01-17T11:50:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-05-26T23:59:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/a38264fc-bf10-4d1f-93c5-ca8952408c39/79480480.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:3,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mMonte Carlo Methods in Finance[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mNon-bankers can learn to understand the mathematical models that have made the headlines so many times in recent years. A course for students of economics, business studies, mathematics, physics and computer science.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m### Learn how to measure the risk of an investment portfolio! [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn this course you will simulate the time evolution of prices of financial assets, use the Black-Scholes model to price European or Asian options and compute the Value-at-Risk of a portfolio. The approach is hands-on with a strong emphasis on practical simulations that you will program, run and explore in your own computer.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mMonte Carlo Methods in Finance[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m will be offered on iversity from 20 January, 2014 until 16 April, 2014.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Structure[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course is structured in 9 chapters[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 1**: Introduction  [2014/01/20  - 2014/01/29][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 2**: Understanding random numbers  [2014/01/30  - 2014/02/05][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 3**: Generating random numbers [2014/02/06 - 2014/02/12][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 4**: Brownian motion [2014/02/13 - 2014/02/26][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 5**: Ordinary differential equations [2014/02/27 - 2014/03/05][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 6**: Stochastic differential equations [2014/03/06 - 2014/03/12][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 7**: Pricing of simple derivative products [2014/03/13 - 2014/03/26][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 8**: Pricing of more complex derivative products [2014/03/27 - 2014/04/02][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Chapter 9**: Modeling and quantifying financial risk [2014/04/03 - 2014/04/16][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapters are divided into units. Each unit consists of a video followed by a quiz. At the end of each chapter you will solve and turn in some homework exercises. In these exercises you will explore additional material on your own and then respond to questions in multiple choice format.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSome of the explanations in the videos and the exercises make reference to short programs that you can download  and execute in your own computer.  You are encouraged  to experiment with  these programs (modify the values of parameters, complete or rewrite the code to alter the model or to implement related functionality)  and run your own simulations. The code provided can be executed in either GNU Octave  or MATLAB.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Certification[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will receive a **certificate of participation** after having completed **at least 75% of the course learning activities** (videos, quizzes and homework). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Learning objectives[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAt the end of this course you will know how to answer the following questions:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn1.  Why are random numbers needed in quantitative finance? And, if they are random, how can they be used to give precise, accurate answers to quantitative financial problems? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn2.  What is the Black-Scholes model?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn3.  What is geometric brownian motion and how can it be used to simulate the evolution of asset prices in financial markets? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn4.  How are Monte Carlo methods used to determine the right price of a derivative product, such as a European call option?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn5.  What is the theory of copulas and how can it be used to model general  dependencies among financial assets?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn6.  How is financial risk modeled, characterized and quantified?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Workload[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will need between 5 and 8 hours of work per week during a total of 12 weeks to complete all the learning activities, including the homework.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Prior knowledge[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course is geared to students not only in economics and finance, but also in mathematics, computer science, engineering, physics and the natural sciences.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo knowledge of finance is required.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBasic knowledge of Calculus (integration and differentiation, Taylor series), Linear Algebra (matrices, determinants, eigenvalues and eigenvectors) and Probability (random variables, probability density and cumulative distribution functions) at an introductory undergraduate level is strongly  recommended.  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProgramming knowledge is recommended. We will be designing simulations that can be executed in either GNU Octave or in Matlab. The programs will be short, intuitive, fully documented and easy to follow. Yet they will be powerful tools under your control, and will allow you to explore, experiment and learn at your own initiative.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Language[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will be taught in English.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Our team[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAna Lozano Valverde, *Think Visual* [video direction and production][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIago L[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xB3[0m[31mpez, [14 pies][1] [video production][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWouter De Vylder [animation][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJasmina Mrkonja [English subtitles][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJuana Calle [administration][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLorenzo Hern[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA1[0m[31mndez, *Quantitative Risk Research, S.L.* [course contents][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJaime Vinuesa, *Quantitative Risk Research, S.L.* [course contents][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAlberto Su[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA1[0m[31mrez, *Universidad Aut[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xB3[0m[31mnoma de Madrid*  [course direction][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSpecial thanks to Profs. Jose Luis Fern[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA1[0m[31mndez P[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA9[0m[31mrez and Santiago Carrillo Men[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA9[0m[31mdez from the Mathematics department at the Universidad Aut[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xB3[0m[31mnoma de Madrid for their input and advice.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###FAQ[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Where can I find the software needed for the course?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe programs used in the course can be executed either in GNU Octave (version  3.6.4) or in MATLAB.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnGNU Octave is freely redistributable software and can be downloaded from [http://www.gnu.org/software/octave/][2]. The version that should be used in Windows is *Octave3.6.4_gcc4.6.2*, which can be retreived at the URL [Octave 3.6.4 for Windows MinGW][3]. Please follow the instructions in that webpage to install the software. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[MATLAB][4] is commercial software and you need to have a valid license to install it in your computer. As a result of support from MathWorks, students will be granted a downloadable license to MATLAB and the recommended toolboxes (Statistics and Optimization) for the duration of the course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Where can I find information on the iversity platform?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at the [iversity FAQ][5] if you have any general questions regarding the platform.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: http://www.14pies.com[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: http://www.gnu.org/software/octave/[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [3]: http://sourceforge.net/projects/octave/files/Octave%20Windows%20binaries/Octave%203.6.4%20for%20Windows%20MinGW%20installer/[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [4]: http://www.mathworks.com/matlab/[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [5]: https://www.iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-01-20T00:01:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-04-30T23:59:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/45d1588f-cfb6-4181-b6c4-ec4d91bc9798/79461800.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:54,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDesigning Resilient Schools[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mHow can architecture help people in times of urgent need caused by natural disasters? In this course, we will design resilient schools that could serve as community centers and shelters for the victims of the devastating typhoon Haiyan in the Philippines.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m###Course Description[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOn November 9, 2013 the devastating typhoon Haiyan hit the Phillipines, causing more than 5,000 deaths and destroying the homes and cities for millions. Natural disasters are happening more and more often due to climate change. We can[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt do much to stop them, but as architects we can help with the recovery and to build shelters that would withstand them.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe goal of this online course is to generate design ideas for resilient schools for the victims of Typhoon Haiyan and other natural disasters. The participants in this course will design schools, which could be implemented by the Department of Education and Architecture for Humanity in the Philippines. We will engage with a team of architects, planners, engineers, and social workers. After the course, the projects and instructions will be placed on the open source platform Open Online Architecture (OOArch.org), so anyone can download and use them. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAn international jury will select the best projects, which will eventually be built. We[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll have weekly lectures and daily discussions on our forum. A team of professors, consultants, and teaching assistants led by Prof. Ivan Shumkov will guide and assist all students in their work.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Schedule[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 1, January 14: Welcome and Introduction[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 2, January 21: Schools and Resilient Architecture[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 3, January 28 : Classroom Unit Design[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 4, February 7: Aggregation and Site Design[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 5, February 14: Resilient School Design[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWeek 7, February 21: Design Submission and Feedback[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Learning Outcomes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents  will learn about resilient architeture and how it can be used in communities in need. They will improve their design and collaboration skills. During the second week of the course, each student will design individual proposals and post them on the forum. All students will be publish their design proposals and ask others for feedback and help on their projects. They will form collaboration teams, which will work together on developing integral projects that include aspects of architectural design, engineering, social space, community development, economical feasibility, sustainability and resilience. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Workload[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe involvement in the course is flexible. For architects, this is meant to be an intensive design studio course, so participants are expected to dedicate 10-20 hours a week. For others, who act as advisors and collaborators, it could take 2-5 hours of work weekly.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Format[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will be organized similar to a competition for design ideas, but will encourage collaborations and teamwork. We will use peer-to-peer review as a way to exchange feedback. We will also have a course forum and team groups on Google+ where students will exchange and discuss design ideas. During the course, the projects will be developed to the phase of schematic design. At the end of the course, the 5-10 best proposals will be selected and further developed with the guidance of the course professor, consultants, and the local authorities. Some of the proposals will eventually be build if funding and local support are secured.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Prior Knowledge[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPrevious experience in design is recommended, but there will be opportunities for others to participate. The course work will be collaboration between people from many different backgrounds: design, engineering, economics, healthcare, social studies. They will share and exchange their knowledge, skills and energy to design solutions that are resilient, feasible, sustainable, buildable, etc.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Consultants and Advisors[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNestor Arabejos, Ecotektonika, Manila[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBea Camacho, Harvard GSD, Philippines[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnXavier Vilalta, XVA Arquitectura, Barcelona[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Final Jury[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnKenneth Frampton, Columbia University, New York[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnGiancarlo Mazzanti, El Equipo de Mazzanti, Bogota[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIllac Angelo Diaz, Architecture for Humanity, Manila[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIvan Shumkov, Open Online Academy, New York[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOthers TBD[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Certification[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAfter completing the course assignments, students will receive a letter of participation according to their role and degree of involvement: architect, designer, project manager, engineer, consultant, advisor, economist, communications, etc. Students who submit the final Resilient School project will be eligible for the official certificate of successful completion of the course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Community[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[OOAc Facebook Page][1][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[DRS Facebook Group][2][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[Google+ Community][3][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[DRS_OOAc, World Map][4][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[OOAc LinkedIn Page][5][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[OOAc LinkedIn Group][6][1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://www.facebook.com/OOAcademy[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://www.facebook.com/groups/336987179777169/[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [3]: https://plus.google.com/u/0/communities/116841709432199568975[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [4]: https://www.zeemaps.com/map?group=813580[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026add=1[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [5]: http://www.linkedin.com/company/5014030?trk=tyah[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026trkInfo=tas:open%20onl,idx:1-1-1[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [6]: http://www.linkedin.com/groups?home=[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026gid=7446122[1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026trk=anet_ug_hm[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-01-14T18:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-03-01T18:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/cb071b75-dd15-496e-93da-0aa4fdad3b82/70136814631520.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:28,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mPublic Privacy: Cyber Security and Human Rights[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mWild, wild web: Is the Internet a lawless no man[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms land? Based on the recent public debate on data protection and massive privacy infringements, this course will explore the connection between cyber security and human rights. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m###Course Description[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mFor the internet to remain global and open, it is imperative that countries, including those currently lacking capacity to adequately deal with security concerns, to adopt a growth- and freedom-oriented, participative, bottom-up perspective on security that has human rights at its core.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m (Joint Governmental Statement at UN Human Rights Council in June 2013) [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnArguably, the internet poses severe challenges to state sovereignty and governmental legitimacy. Governments around the world find it increasingly difficult to control, regulate or monitor the massive flow of data within the cyber-world and uphold human rights and fundamental freedoms at the same time. Nevertheless, the world wide web is one of the main prerequisites for economic growth and democracy. It enables citizen participation , engagements and inter-action on all levels that can lead to social transformation and political change. Radical groups, democracy movements, development organizations and human rights NGOs all use the internet to further their goals. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSince the former NSA contractor, Edward Snowden, released a variety of confidential documents we all know of PRISM, TEMPORA and other programs and their massive privacy infringements. These programs were primarily designed to collect user data to increase the capability of intelligence services to protect societies from internal and external threats. But are those programs not undermining essential citizen freedoms and fundamental human rights? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis course systematically examines the compliance between international human rights norms, standards and mechanism  within  legal and political frameworks and the growing cyber security regime. Debates about the loss of state sovereignty over cyber security, paired with the idea of internet freedom and users[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31m and citizens[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31m responsibility lead to the question, whether individual and state responsibility based on reciprocity and human rights compliance are reconcilable. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Learning Outcomes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents taking this course will learn:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m how human rights are used in the debate about Public Privacy [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m how individual, societal, political and governmental actors interact in this context[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA2[0m[31m what cyber security in consistency with human rights is about.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnUsing this information, students will practice assessing and analyzing cyber security issues based on international human rights norms, standards and regimes.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Structure[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe first part of the course will provide an overview of the current state of international and regional human rights regimes and their efforts to protect freedom rights while also ensuring private security. The second part will then go into the evolution of human rights, their violations and protection mechanism in era of the internet. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 1: An Introduction to Public Privacy, Cyber Space and Human Rights[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 2: Human Rights - Yours and the Rights of Others[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 3: Human Rights Cyber Regime[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 4: Governance in Cyber Space[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 5: Security [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Surveillance in Cyber Space[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 6: E-Governance [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 E-Democracy[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 7: State Sovereignty vs. Public Privacy[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChapter 8: Cyber Justice through Public Privacy [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Wrap Up of the MOOC Course[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Format[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will be hosted online and will consist of lectures by the instructor, as well as guest lectures and exclusive interviews with respective stakeholders. Additional reading material, animations and images will support each learning objective. Students will be assessed through quizzes, peer-to-peer review and their participation in interactive discussion forums.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###FAQ[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at the [FAQ][1] if you have any general questions regarding the platform.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1]: https://www.iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2013-12-04T15:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-02-26T15:03:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/c6362a1e-b4fe-44ac-8861-312350f4f78b/79488940.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:2,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDesign 101 (or Design Basics) Online Course[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDesign your own world. Are you ready? This MOOC is a journey into contemporary design through 101 exercises. Learn by doing and transform your everyday life into 101 projects.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDesign is foremost a language. A language shared, talked and discussed by designers all over the world.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThings, people and places we all know about.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo discover more about the Design 101 mindset, you can follow our course preparation on [Facebook][1], [Twitter][2] and [YouTube][3]. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIt would be nice to receive your feedback! [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Design your own world. Are you ready?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDesign 101 is a journey into contemporary design in which you will transform yourself and your everyday life into 101 projects. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFor three months, you will develop basic design attitudes that will allow you to thrive in today[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms world, while restoring your understanding of its mechanics. We live in a global community where the physical bits are slowly (and not so slowly) overlapped by social media. Design has become #design. Indeed, the use of new technologies has changed the teaching and, by the same token, the nature of the past; the past is being renewed. Herein lies the conceptual hinge of Design 101: [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mna new way to learn a new design.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTo do so, we will collectively explore the tools of today (such as this MOOC platform) to step into a fantastic voyage through time and space, in which we are all absolute beginners.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###How?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDesign is everything. Design is objects, buildings, sports, games[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\xA6[0m[31mour lives.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJohan Cruyff, a very famous footballer and fantastic designer, once said:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn*[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mI never practice tricks. I play very simply. That's what it's all about. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlaying simple football is the hardest thing.[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m*[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mt[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**very simply**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnEveryday, you will receive a special package from a different place along our journey. The package will introduce objects, characters and happenings that are intertwined with the narrative of the course. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnEach bundle will include 2 main elements: [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - An animated postcard announcing the day[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms brief.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - A letter exploring subjects in depth with the use of links, books, movies, music and more.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**on a weekly basis**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnEach week, there is a new unit consisting of seven postcards/briefs outlining a few simple activities to trigger your imagination. From 15 minutes to one hour of work per day at the most. The quicker, the better![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOn Mondays, you get an overview of the week and a quiz to complete.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, following our input, you start working. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBy Sunday, you will upload images of what you made during the week.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will refer, think and create a lot of different things. Not easy, but surely fun![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur special trip will end with a three-day festival: a special event in a special place to exhibit your work to the public and get to know your travel mates.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**forum: questions and answers**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDoubts, ideas, whatever comes to mind. It is a perfect place to get entangled into discussions and become a true actor within the community.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn the design world, questions are much more interesting than answers. This is why the best questions asked in this forum will be redirected to a Design 101 e-book, to be printed at the end of the course. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**extra! extra! encyclopedia!**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf you are of the curious kind, we have a special page with all the people, places, things mentioned throughout the course. We could consider it our mini-encyclopedia. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOnce we have a shared vocabulary/language, things become meaningful. Conversations start up quickly and flow nicely.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLike any other language, [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mdesign[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m is in constant change. Our mini-encyclopedia is a great foundation upon which to build your own collection of references.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Dates[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will officially start on October 28, 2013 and end on February 5, 2014. However, the course will remain [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mopen[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m until April 20, 2014 (to give you more time to complete the homework).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Content of the course/journey:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe various things to do (so-called [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mhands-on[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m activities) will be divided into 14 units, one per week.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn1. Intro: Acquaint yourself with the course[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms dynamics.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn2. Myself: Represent one's self.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn3. My diary: Learn about the design process by creating a very simple object.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn4. Kitchen Stories: Become an expert at something and develop basic social skills.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn5. Visiting You: Look back at what we have done so far.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn6. It[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31ms alive: Design as a garden. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn7. Voyage into my room: Understand interior spaces, plans and measures. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn8. Making things: Get familiar with shapes, colors, materials. Plan a series.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn9. Christmas break: Lots of greetings + some more.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn10. Zoom out (the city): Observe the public space in a new way (and map it).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn11. Telling stories: Form doesn[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt follow function. Form follows fiction.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn12. Dressing people: Understand what [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9C[0m[31mcustom-made[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x9D[0m[31m really means.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn13. Road to nowhere: Learn to become self-sufficient.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn14. Ready to show? Ready to exhibit?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Learning objectives[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDesign 101 will help you understand:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- How the world looks through the special lenses called [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mdesign[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- Who shares your visions and ideas (who could collaborate with you in the future). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- How a community works: its behavior and potential.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- What skills and attitudes you have: their merits and limitations. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Prior knowledge[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo prior knowledge is required. If you have a lot of prior knowledge, it might make the learning process more difficult, but don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt worry, no one is perfect. As we said, if we talk about contemporary design, we are all [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mabsolute beginners[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn----[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Questions or comments?  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWrite to Ms. Lola (our so-called secretary, but actually the real boss of this whole venture) at: design101.info@gmail.com[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThen, you can follow Stefano Mirti on [Twitter][4], [Facebook][5], [Instagram][6]. He would love to hear from you! [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###The platform[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at the [FAQ][7] if you have any general questions regarding the platform.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[7]: https://www.iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Credits[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnCourse by: Stefano Mirti and Anne-Sophie Gauvin with Lucia Giuliano and Giovanni Pasca Raymondi[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnWith: Giulia San Gregorio, Lola de la Arena[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnGraphics: Marco Agosta, Alica Horvathova, Andrea Molteni[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnVideo: Pierluigi Anselmi, Carlo Altera[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSound: Duccio Servi[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDesign 101, a whoami production for Iversity. A collaboration between the Abadir Academy of Fine Arts and IdLab.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [1]: https://www.facebook.com/design1o1[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [2]: https://twitter.com/design1o1[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [3]: http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCu_Cu5Z4-rSCRwbx45QzdIw[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [4]: https://twitter.com/stefi_idlab[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [5]: https://www.facebook.com/stefano.mirti.3?fref=ts[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn  [6]: http://instagram.com/stefi_idlab[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2013-10-28T08:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-02-05T10:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/05a90190-bb6a-4ff3-ac25-c15910979e0e/70366102507480.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:20,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mContemporary Architecture Online Course[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mThe course analyzed major contemporary architectural ideas and projects in the context of globalization. We traced the development of architecture since the 1990s by discussing some of the most important topics and influential architects of our time.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mOur course will analyze major contemporary architectural ideas, ideologies, and projects in the context of both globalization and specific local contexts. We will trace the development of architecture since the early 90s by discussing the work of some of the most influential architects of our time. The critical reflection on contemporary topics will allow students to better understand the buildings and cities which we live in. When talking about the architectural protagonists of today, we will focus on their most recent work. Some references will be made to their earlier work, but the focus will be on how they adapt their thinking to current design tendencies. We will examine the evolution of their work and at the same time try to understand how they react to current challenges and opportunities in our profession and society.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Course Schedule[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 1** (15/10/13) **Globalization and Critical Regionalism**: Rafael Moneo, Steven Holl; Design and Online Education, Behind the Scenes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 2** (22/10/13) **Tectonic, Technology and Structure**: Renzo Piano, Richard Rogers, Norman Foster[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 3** (29/10/13) **Critical Discourse and Architecture**: Rem Koolhaas, Peter Eisenmann, Bernard Tschumi[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 4** (05/11/13) **Surface, Materiality, and Ornament**: Herzog [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 De Meuron, Jean Nouvel, SANAA  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe **Midterm Exam** will start on **November 7**, 2013 and run for 10 days. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Virtual Classroom #1** on **November 8** at 10am NYC time, 4pm CET.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 5** (12/11/13) **Midterm assignments** are due before 11:59pm CET on **November 17**  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Virtual Classroom #2** on **November 15** at 10am NYC time, 4pm CET. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**NYC Architectural Tour** on November 16 at 3pm will start in Washington Square. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 6** (19/11/13) **Peer-to-peer evaluations** are due before 11:59pm CET on **November 24**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 7** (26/11/13) **Form, Sign and Sculpture**: Frank Gehry, Daniel Libeskind, Santiago Calatrava [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 8** (10/12/13) **Digital Design and Computation**: UN Studio, FOA, Zaha Hadid[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 9** (16/12/13) **Sustainability and Resilience**: Wiliam McDonough, Kongjian Yu, Norman Foster, Worldchanging[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 10** (25/12/13) **Social Design and Activism**: Medellin, Bogota, Giancarlo Mazzanti, Exhibitions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 11** (06/01/14) **Final Exam** starts on January 6 and is due at 6pm CET on **January 13**  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Final Video Assignment** starts on December 30 and is due at 6pm CET on **January 13**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn - **Week 12** (13/01/14)**Peer-to-peer evaluations** are due before 6pm CET on **January 20**  [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe **Course Certificate** will be awarded on **February 10, 2014**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will offer **Virtual Classroom** videoconference every Friday at 10am NYC time (4pm CET). [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Exercises and Assignments[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnStudents will do research and critical analysis of architecture. They will analyze and comment on the projects presented in each chapter of the course. They will also explore buildings in the cities where they live and visit, according to the concepts introduced in the course, by taking pictures and making videos. The work will be posted every week on the course forum and discussed with others. A selection of the best projects and posts will be featured in an exhibit after completing the course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###What will you learn?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will introduce participants to the contemporary architecture scene and allow them to position themselves into it. Students will acquire the essential skills for looking at, analyzing and understanding architecture. The final goal is to turn use architecture as a way to look at the places that we inhabit, an action for positive change, and a generator of a vision for making possible worlds.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Our basic questions[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn1.[1;35m\\[0m[31mtWhat are current trends in architecture?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn2.[1;35m\\[0m[31mtWho are the protagonists that shape our cities?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn3.[1;35m\\[0m[31mtWhat can architecture do to improve our living conditions?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn4.[1;35m\\[0m[31mtWhat are the most significant buildings of our time?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn5.[1;35m\\[0m[31mtHow can we improve the quality of life in our cities?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Who is this course for and what prior knowledge do you need?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course is both for the general public and for people with experience in architecture, so any person can take it. Basic knowledge of architecture is recommended but not necessary. If you are already a student of architecture, this would be a way to expand and further your studies in a global context. If you are already an architect you can learn about the recent developments of the profession and be inspired for your work. if you have general cultural curiosity about architecture, this course will introduce you to some basic concepts that would allow you to understand better the values and importance of architecture.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###How much will you have to work? [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLiving in the world of architecture is a full-time job, but you[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mll have to spend 2-3 hours per week with your computer and a few more exploring your city. The final assignment will take a few days to complete if you want to qualify for the exposition.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Certification[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou will receive a certificate for the course after you complete all the assignments. If you include it in your CV, remember that the course is offered by [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mOpen Online Academy, New York.[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Study groups and tours[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course will feature guided virtual tours and study groups. Students will be encouraged to set up Meetups in their cities and universities to discuss the course content.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###FAQ[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease have a look at the [FAQ][1] if you have any general questions regarding the platform.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1]:https://www.iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Sign, Like, Share, Tweet and Stay tuned[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLike  **OOAc on Facebook**: https://www.facebook.com/OOAcademy [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnLike  our **Course on Facebook**: https://www.facebook.com/ContemporaryArchitectureMOOC [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAdd your location on **our World Map**: https://www.zeemaps.com/map?group=698881 [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJoin our **Google+ Community**: https://plus.google.com/u/0/communities/104032017567426934688[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnSupport our online course: http://igg.me/at/ArchitectureMOOC/x/5353594[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2013-10-15T00:01:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2014-02-01T00:00:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/9037d20d-acff-48f9-af1f-b1414f784f18/79479600.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:6,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mThe Future of Storytelling - Online Course[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mLearn how to analyze, contextualize and create stories and narratives in current media: from understanding storytelling basics to discussing new online tools and formats, this course brings together a network of media researchers, creators, and students.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mAre you interested in the mechanics of current fiction formats? Do you want to know how stories are told? Do you want to analyze, understand, contextualize and create stories and narratives? Then join our MOOC and share our passion for storytelling![1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###What to Expect[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTogether with a whole network of media researchers, creators and students we will:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- learn storytelling basics such as antagonist/protagonist relationships, narrative/narrated time, ...[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- have a look at exciting current media projects[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- analyze how they are designed and executed based on aforementioned basics[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- and discuss how (and if) new online tools and formats change the way stories are told and perceived.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe 8-chapter course starts on October 25th, 2013 and ends on December 20th, 2013. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**(Please review the updated FAQ below in case you have questions.)**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIt offers weekly video material, lessons, interviews and tasks on the following topics (not necessarily in this order):[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- storytelling basics[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- serial formats (on the TV, web and beyond)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- storytelling in role-playing games[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- interactive storytelling in video games[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- transmedia storytelling[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- alternate-reality gaming[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- augmented reality and location-based storytelling[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- the role of tools, interfaces and information architectures in current storytelling.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur first Storytelling-MOOC will focus on fictional formats.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Inspire and Help Understand[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur goal is to inspire and help understand. To broaden our horizon of what is and might be possible and what has already been attempted, and what has succeeded or even failed - and why.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIn several little tasks you'll analyze and practice storytelling on your own and in teams.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Why this MOOC is Interdisciplinary[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBased at the Design Department at the University of Applied Sciences Potsdam, this MOOC is not only interdisciplinary, but also includes guest lectures and project presentations by game designers, writers, transmedia producers, TV makers, executives and theorists from many different fields of study. We will thus be able to discuss content, structures and technologies from various perspectives.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Learning Outcomes[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOur MOOC will help you answer the following questions:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn1. How do fictional stories work? Which structures and mechanics are used?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn2. How do new technologies influence the ways stories are told and perceived - and which new media formats have been developed during the last years?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn3. How can technologies, interfaces and visuals engage an audience fast and continuously?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn4. How can I develop and implement my own story-ideas - on my own or in teams?[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Prior Knowledge[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo prior knowledge of storytelling mechanics is needed, but can be helpful.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnInterest in creative processes and new technologies is welcome and encouraged.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- You don't know what an alternate-reality game, RPG or transmedia storytelling is? - Great, you'll learn it here.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- You are a storytelling professional? - Great, we hope to inspire you. Please feel free to help us inspire others by sharing interesting links, events and projects on our Facebook page.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFor updates and more on our MOOC go to: https://www.facebook.com/TheFutureOfStorytellingMooc (You do not need a FB-account to be able to read all the posts and see all pictures!)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnPlease add yourself to our StoryMOOC map where you can see people from your area: https://www.zeemaps.com/map?group=695139[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnTwitter: @crossmedienne @julianvandieken #storymooc[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###StoryMOOC-Team[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProf. Winfried Gerling (Concepts [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Aesthetics of New Media, Dean of the Design Department | StoryMOOC Co-Creator)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProf. Constanze Langer (Visual Interface Design | StoryMOOC Co-Creator)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnChristina Maria Schollerer (Research Associate [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Freelance Writer | StoryMOOC Co-Creator)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJulian van Dieken (Filmmaker [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Director | StoryMOOC Co-Creator)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnBernadette Klausberger (Project Management)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnJannes Schwentuchowski (Student Assistant |Content Management)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnAlexandra Schulz (Community Management)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn###Guest Lecturers[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnRebecca Ahlen [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m Head of Digital | Ufa Serial Drama (Chapter 2/3)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDr. Mark Butler [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m Media Theorist [1;35m\\[0m[31mu0026 Futurologist | Digital Games Research Center, University of Potsdam (5)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnProf. Dr. Jan Distelmeyer [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m History and Theory of Technical Media, University of Applied Sciences Potsdam (3/4)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDes Doyle [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m Director of the upcoming documentary [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mShowrunners[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m (2)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnCornelia Funke [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m Best-selling Author of the Mirrorworld and Inkheart Series (1/7/8)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnMaria Grau Stenzel [1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x93[0m[31m Project Manager at Honig Studios | Co-Creator of [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mMilli - a little, big journey around the world[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m (1/4/7/8)[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35