n**Can I still enroll?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNo, unfortunately enrollments were only possible until December 20th. All content will be available here for those enrolled for at least 1 year. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Is there any other chance to get to the content of this course?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYes, all video lectures and interviews are to be uploaded on our YouTube-Channel http://www.youtube.com/user/officialStoryMOOC for those who couldn't follow the course on iversity in time.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Will there be certificates?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYES! Statements of Participation will be available from Friday, Feb 21st onwards for any participant who has completed the course by 80% or more.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThis means:[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- if you **already gathered more than 80%**: Congratulations! In this case you have earned your Statement of Participation for the MOOC already, and can download it on Friday (or later) from the iversity course website (once logged in).[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn- if you have **not** finished the course yet: Don[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mt worry, you still have time to go through all the videos, quizzes,... thoroughly until at least December 2014, and download your Statement of Participation once you[1;35m\xE2[0m[31m[1;35m\x80[0m[31m[1;35m\x99[0m[31mre done.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**What does MOOC stand for?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIt means [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mMassive Open Online Course[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**What does this course consist of?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThe course is based on recorded video lectures, quizzes and creative tasks that will be online from October 25th here on our course website on http://iversity.org/courses/the-future-of-storytelling. From October 25th onwards, a new video lecture will be launched every Friday for 8 weeks at 10am CET. If you're enrolled this means: you'll be able to access the videos from then on for at least the 8 following weeks, not just at 10am.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**How much time will I need to participate?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnFrom just watching the video lessons (about 20-60 min per week) to engaging in discussions and tasks (about 2-4 hours per week), exploring our reading list and even presenting your own current projects via essays or video link on our Facebook page, your involvement is entirely up to you. The more you engage yourself, the more you gain.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Will there be graded assignments?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnThere is weekly homework (Creative Tasks) that you are very well invited but not obliged to do to complete this course. There will be no graded/peer-graded assessments/exams. Our aim is to inspire, give input and offer a stage to discuss and work together with many others who share the passion for storytelling. So: What you make out of it, how much you get involved, is up to you. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Is this course only available in English?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYes, for now. Due to technical and production time restrictions, we will only be able to offer this first MOOC in ONE language. As English is the language most applying students here share, we decided to go for it. However, we uploaded our videos on our YouTube channel http://www.youtube.com/user/officialStoryMOOC, were they can be subtitled using AMARA.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**My written English is not that good. Can I still participate in the tasks?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnOf course! Although language is an important part of storytelling in general, great works have been created without even a single audible word (e.g. silent movies). We are working on making our tasks as language-independent as possible. Good grammar and spelling skills are not the only key to succeeding in this course.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**How much time do I have to complete the tasks?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnMost tasks are designed to help you experiment with storytelling. They are useful for YOU whenever you do them. To make them count for the course, however, tasks given usually can be worked on for a week and they are due the following Friday, again 10am CET. [1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**How can I connect with other students?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnYou can visit our Facebook-Page https://www.facebook.com/TheFutureOfStorytellingMooc (no FB-account necessary to read and see all posts) and/or use #storymooc at Twitter to connect with other StoryMOOCers. Also: Feel free to create your own meeting spots/blogs (that you are most comfortable with) if you want.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**Will there be a second edition/run of this course?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnNot for now. Although we would love to create and host a so-to-speak [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m2nd season[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m of this MOOC, there are no definite plans yet. This experience will therefore be unique for now.[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn**What do I do if I have questions that are not answered here?**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf you have technical questions concerning the iversity-platform/enrollments, please have a look at the [FAQ][1].[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1]: https://www.iversity.org/pages/faq[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnIf you have any more questions concerning the content of our course or great ideas you want to share: You can always post on our Facebook-Page and ask the community in case our team is not available. Once the course starts, additional discussion options go live right here on the course page.[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstart_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2013-10-25T10:00:00.000+02:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mend_date[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m2013-12-20T17:45:00.000+01:00[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mstate[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31marchived[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mimage[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mhttps://d1wshrh2fwv7ib.cloudfront.net/courses/90b6d5e9-c0f9-4a75-9b8a-cb034c3aff15/79475540.jpg[1;35m\"[0m[31m},{[1;35m\"[0m[31mid[1;35m\"[0m[31m:231,[1;35m\"[0m[31mtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mEinf[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xBC[0m[31mhrung in die Arbeitspsychologie[1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31msubtitle[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31mDer Kurs [1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31mEinf[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xBC[0m[31mhrung in die Arbeitspsychologie[1;35m\\[0m[31m[1;35m\"[0m[31m vermittelt dir das Grundwissen und die wichtigsten Konzepte der Arbeitspsychologie. [1;35m\"[0m[31m,[1;35m\"[0m[31mdescription[1;35m\"[0m[31m:[1;35m\"[0m[31m####**Kurszusammenfassung**[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mn[1;35m\\[0m[31mr[1;35m\\[0m[31mnDer Kurs f[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xBC[0m[31mhrt ein in die Fragestellungen der modernen Arbeitspsychologie. Er vermittelt das Grundwissen und die wichtigsten Konzepte und Interventionsmethoden der Arbeitspsychologie. Am Anfang steht die Kl[1;35m\xC3[0m[31m[1;35m\xA4[0m[31mrung der wichtigsten Begriffe: Was ist Psychologie b